the hair and scalp.<br />\\r\\n9)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Try Cold Water Showers: &nbsp;<br />\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hot water has the tendency to dry out our skin, so it&rsquo;s best to use cold water to tighten your cuticles and pores, which will prevent them from getting clogged. Cold water can &ldquo;seal&rdquo; the pores in the skin and scalp too, preventing dirt from getting in.<br />\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;I begin with warm water and do a 30-60 second cold water finish at the end of my shower. &nbsp;It is quite invigorating and great for the skin and hair. &nbsp;You can read more about this.&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n10)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Take a Collagen Supporting Product: &nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>\\r\\n', 15, 49, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/beautifulskin.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/527325_resized734114.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(231, 'Day 3: Toning The Arms Workout {~20 minutes)', 'Day 3: Toning The Arms Workout {~20 minutes)', '20 Shoulder Presses\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Hold a pair of dumbbells in a neutral grip at about shoulder height.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your chest up and shoulder blades down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Push the arms up overhead in a controlled fashion.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Fully extend them and then slowly bring them back down to starting position.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Do 20 repetitions.\r\n\\r\\n20 Dips\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Place you hands on a couch, table or chair and keep your butt close to it.&nbsp;\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your feet as far from your hands as possible.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; To make it easier, bring your feet closer to your hands.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your chest up and your shoulders down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend from the elbows creating a 90 degree angle, then extend the elbows and go all the way up.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Squeeze your triceps (back of the arm) and then slowly and controlled go back down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Do 20 reps.\r\n\\r\\n20 Hammer Curls\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Stand with your chest up and shoulders down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hold a pair of dumbbells at your sides in a neutral grip (palms in).\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bend from the elbow as if you want the dumbbell to touch your shoulders.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Squeeze the biceps (front of arms) and then lower the weights slowly and controlled.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Repeat for 20 reps.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/82566_resized620241.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(232, 'Day 5: Leg Slimming Thighs Workout {~20 minutes)', 'Day 5: Leg Slimming Thighs Workout {~20 minutes)', '20 Squats\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stand with your feet a little wider than shoulder width apart. As far as if comfortable for you.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Hold dumbbells at your side or just use your body weight.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your chest up and shoulders down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend from the hips and knees as if you were going to sit down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Go as close to 90 degrees as you can.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Arch your back as you go down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Go down slowly and controlled.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Go back up, extend your hips and knees and squeeze your BOOTY!\r\n\\r\\n20 Deadlifts\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stand with your feet a little wider than shoulder width apart. As far as if comfortable for you.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Hold dumbbells in front of you\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your chest up and shoulders down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend from the hips keeping your shoulders back and face forward.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend as much as you can without bending from the spine (back) don&#39;t round the lower back.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Imagine your hips are a hinge on a door, bend from the hip and do it slowly and controlled.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Come back up and squeeze the back of the legs and butt.\r\n\\r\\n20 Lunges\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Place one leg in front of the other.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; The back foot should remain on the ball of the foot\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend down as low as you can, keeping your hips in and keeping your weight back.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Keep your chest up and stay nice and straight.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Go back up by extending the hips and knees and squeeze the back leg flute (butt) and front of leg.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Repeat for 20 reps and then switch sides.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/334720_resized698562.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(233, 'Day 6-7: Rest', 'Day 6-7: Rest', 'Day 6-7: Rest\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/558075_resized629099.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(234, 'Day 2: Pregnancy Cardio Workout', 'Day 2: Pregnancy Cardio Workout', 'It&#39;s a CARDIO DAY today!\r\n\\r\\nYou only need 15-20 minutes.\r\n\\r\\nCan you do that?\r\n\\r\\nRemember, if you would rather go to a gym or a group class for your cardio that is totally ok!\r\n\\r\\nYou can also go outside for a jog.\r\n\\r\\nI just like these CARDIO HIIT WORKOUTS because they are fun, they go by so much faster and I don&#39;t have to go any where.\r\n\\r\\nMake sure you have eaten some protein and carbs at least an hour before you workouts and that you have your post-workout meal or smoothie for after.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/724939_resized744018.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(235, 'Day 3: Pregnancy Toned Arms Workout', 'Day 3: Pregnancy Toned Arms Workout', '20 Front Raises\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Start with your arms in front of you holding a pair of weights.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Palms facing your legs.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Keeping your chest up and your shoulder blades down, lift your arms to shoulder height.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Keep the arms as straight as you can, a very slight bend in the elbow.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Nice and controlled, bring the arms back down to the starting position.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Repeat\r\n\\r\\n20 Triceps Kickbacks\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bend over from the hips and keep your chest up and shoulder down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Back should be almost parallel to the ground.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Hold a pair of dumbbells in a neutral position (palms in)\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Lift the arm a little and from the elbow, extend the arm and squeeze the triceps (back of arm).\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bring the arm back to beginning position and repeat.\r\n\\r\\n20 Bicep Curls\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stand with your chest up and shoulders down.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Hold a pair of dumbbells at your sides palms facing up.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Bend from the elbow as if you want the dumbbell to touch your shoulders.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Squeeze the biceps (front of arms) and then lower the weights slowly and controlled.\r\n\\r\\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Repeat for 20 reps.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/160979_resized961089.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(236, 'Day 4: Pregnancy Cardio Workout', 'Day 4: Pregnancy Cardio Workout', 'It&#39;s a CARDIO DAY today!\r\n\\r\\nYou only need 15-20 minutes.\r\n\\r\\nCan you do that?\r\n\\r\\nRemember, if you would rather go to a gym or a group class for your cardio that is totally ok!\r\n\\r\\nYou can also go outside for a jog.\r\n\\r\\nI just like these CARDIO HIIT WORKOUTS because they are fun, they go by so much faster and I don&#39;t have to go any where.\r\n\\r\\nMake sure you have eaten some protein and carbs at least an hour before you workouts and that you have your post-workout meal or smoothie for after.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 96, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2019-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/first-trimester-pregnancy-workout-tone-tighten copy.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/707144_resized681237.jpg', 0, 'True'),
