(404, 'Is It Okay to Eat Right Before a Workout?', 'Two experts weigh in on when and what you should eat before hitting the gym.', '<h3><em>Myth #1</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Eating before a workout doesn&rsquo;t make sense if I&rsquo;m trying to lose weight.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>The math checks out&mdash;shouldn&#39;t less calories going in mean fewer extra pounds? Mancella explained that while on paper, this is true, that &ldquo;weight loss&rdquo; that happens solely from calorie depletion isn&rsquo;t the type of weight loss most of us are looking for. &ldquo;When we focus on just restricting energy consumption, that weight loss, especially at the beginning, is water weight,&rdquo; she told&nbsp;MensHealth.com. &ldquo;That isn&rsquo;t helping us lose fat or build lean muscle mass.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>BOTTOM LINE:</strong>&nbsp;Even if your goal is weight loss, eating before exercising will help you get more from your effort. Having more successful workouts will help build more muscle and burn more fat.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Eating before a workout is only important if I&rsquo;m doing cardio.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Seem ridiculous to eat before a 40-minute lifting session? It shouldn&rsquo;t. &ldquo;You need carbohydrates in order to lift hard,&rdquo; Spano explained. &ldquo;I can&rsquo;t really think of a workout where it wouldn&rsquo;t be helpful to have eaten carbohydrates beforehand.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Mancella agreed. &ldquo;The point of eating before a workout is to provide energy to perform at a higher level&mdash;lift heavier weights, work faster and harder,&rdquo; she said.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>BOTTOM LINE:</strong>&nbsp;It doesn&rsquo;t matter if you&rsquo;re going for a short HIIT session or a long cardio session, eating before will give you the energy you need to crush it.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2022-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/sportsman-eating-protein-bar-and-using-mobile-phone-royalty-free-image-908963662-1548514300.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/864842_resized15302.jpg', 0, 'True');
