(405, 'The 5-Minute Manicure Every Guy Should Give Himself', 'Occasional clipping just doesn’t cut it', '<p>Walking around with grimy nails and crusty cuticles is downright gross. But it takes a mega-secure man to sit confidently in a nail salon for a professional manicure.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Good for that guy if he doesn&rsquo;t give a crap, but we don&rsquo;t blame you if you prefer to primp in the privacy of your own home.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>That&rsquo;s why we&rsquo;re teaching you the tricks of the trade from the&nbsp;<em>Men&rsquo;s Health</em>&nbsp;associate fashion editor Dan Michel.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Related:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.menshealthbettermanproject.com/?cid=BWO_mh.com_textlink_betterman&amp;keycode=253103\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">The&nbsp;<em>Men&rsquo;s Health</em>&nbsp;Better Man Project&mdash;2,000+ Quick Tricks For Living Your Healthiest Life</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Not convinced that anyone notices your nasty nails? &ldquo;It&rsquo;s a small detail that people actually pay attention to,&rdquo; says Michel.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Think about it: Shaking hands with someone is often your first point of contact with them. What kind of first impression would jagged edges and bleeding cuticles make? &nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The best time to take care of the nails is after you get out of the shower, since they&rsquo;re naturally softer and easier to cut.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve toweled off, follow these three super simple steps for a DIY manicure.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>(When you&rsquo;re done, consider a full-body clean up. Learn the best way to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/grooming/g19547093/7-must-follow-manscaping-tricks/\\\">Groom Your Guy Parts</a>.)</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Step 1: Shape The Nails</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Grab a nail clipper (<a href=\\\"http://www.tweezerman.com/store/product/stainless-steel-fingernail-clipper/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">tweezerman.com</a>) and use the white tip of your nail as a guide to avoid cutting too close.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You want to position the clipper so that only a sliver of white is still visible. Without pushing too hard, cut straight across the nail, leaving the edges sharp.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>(Resist smoothing out the corners, since clipping too close around the edges can lead to ingrown nails.)</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Next, rest an emery board (<a href=\\\"http://www.revlon.com/products/beauty-tools/manicure/compact-emery-boards#309972333100%7C%7C0\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">revlon.com</a>) on the nail and, starting from one corner, file it repeatedly in one direction. Round the corners slightly and continue until you can feel the file start to rub against your skin.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Step 2: Clean Up Around The Edges</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It&rsquo;s tempting to peel off the white gunk around your cuticles with your fingers, but simply yanking it out can cause bleeding and swelling that&rsquo;ll leave your hands in worse shape than before.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Get rid of any excess skin by pinching it with a cuticle nipper (<a href=\\\"http://www.tweezerman.com/store/product/regency-finish-cuticle-nipper/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">tweezerman.com</a>).&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If your cuticles are in pretty good shape, you can stop here. But if they still look mangled, you can use a metal tool to gently push them back (<a href=\\\"http://www.tweezerman.com/store/product/pushy-and-nail-cleaner/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">tweezerman.com</a>).&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Related:&nbsp;</strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/style/g19538109/best-manscaping-survival-tools/\\\">8 Manscaping Survival Tools</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Step 3: Hydrate</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once you&rsquo;re done, rinse your hands and slather them up with a heavy-duty moisturizer to sooth any dry skin. &nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>An extra thick cream will help keep your skin hydrated for longer. Try the Industrial Strength Hand Healer from Jack Black (<a href=\\\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576254&amp;xs=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.getjackblack.com%2FProducts%2FIndustrial-Strength-Hand-Healer-with-Vitamins-A-and-E__4002O.aspx&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.menshealth.com%2Fstyle%2Fa19547524%2Fguy-manicure%2F\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">getjackblack.com</a>).&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/thinkstockphotos-479986338-1485977041.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/630742_resized950245.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(406, 'A Ridiculous Bet Helped This Former Pro Runner Lose 45 Pounds', 'He saved himself from the dumbest tattoo ever.', '<p><em>In February 2017, retired elite runner Colin McCourt went for his first run in five years: a challenging 20-minute shuffle, at a pace just over 12-minutes per mile, through the London streets near his home. The former 14-minute&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.runnersworld.com/training/a24066971/5k-best-distance-to-race/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">5K finisher</a>&nbsp;had spent his post-competition years sitting behind a desk, eating fast food, and drinking a few too many pints in the evening. Looking in the mirror, he saw a too-old, too-heavy man. He barely recognized himself.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Back from&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.runnersworld.com/beginner/a25645864/new-fit-runner/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">that first run</a>, he posted on Instagram about how humbling, painful, and frustrating it was. &ldquo;My legs rubbed and I needed a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.runnersworld.com/sports-bras/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">sports bra</a>.&rdquo; To his horror, his ex-training partners started a group chat to harass him about how out of shape he&rsquo;d become. The texts flew for a solid five hours. The group made a bet: McCourt had to run a sub-16-minute 5K by the end of 2017 or have all 17 of his friends&rsquo; names tattooed on him in Times New Roman. If he did break 16 minutes, they would each pay him &pound;100 (about $128).He giddily agreed to their terms. What kind of fool would turn down $2,200? Then he spent the night in a cold sweat thinking about what he had just agreed to. &ldquo;My body was aching and now I had less than a year to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a25646745/running-for-weight-loss/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">lose about 45 pounds</a>&nbsp;in order to run sub-16,&rdquo; he says.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>After a few casual 5Ks in the 17-minute range, McCourt arrived at the Podium 5K in Preston, England on November 18, 2017. He didn&rsquo;t invite any of his friends to watch, or even let them know he was doing it, for fear they would get in his head. Lining up, McCourt wondered if he could finish in time even without their interference. But once he took off, his nerves settled, and he set a blistering pace to cross the finish line in 15:38.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>He texted his friends his bank details and said, &ldquo;That&rsquo;s for the money boys!&rdquo; He didn&rsquo;t stop smiling for about a month. His candid, frequently hilarious, account of his own transformation gained a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.instagram.com/colinmccourt/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">14,100-strong Instagram following</a>. He now uses the platform to encourage others in their running journeys. He&rsquo;s also focused on 5Ks and 10Ks, continues to set personal goals and, of course, takes on &ldquo;wee competitions&rdquo; with his friends.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Colin&rsquo;s Tips for Coming Back to Running After Taking Years Off</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Take your time:</strong>&nbsp;I started by walking combined with slow jogging. It&rsquo;s a months-long process, and you have to meet your fitness where it is, one day at a time.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Just do something:&nbsp;</strong>We overcomplicate running. Even if you just shuffle around the track for 20 minutes that&rsquo;s better than just thinking about it. [<a href=\\\"https://order.hearstproducts.com/subscribe/hstproducts/237345?utm_campaign=socialflowFBMH&amp;utm_source=facebook&amp;utm_medium=social-media&amp;fbclid=IwAR0OHOAod-vem3rERDFFNmwSxRXhNDj_z0MqK3Jhp9aEeSuvzWBBvLvnYfI&amp;source=socialflowFBMH&amp;utm_content=a26007043\\\">Runner&rsquo;s World 10-Minute Cross-Training</a>, gives you five muscle-building routines that take just 10 minutes to get you stronger.]</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Mix it up:</strong>&nbsp;Work on gaining your overall fitness back through high-intensity cross-training at least once a week (rowing, cycling, swimming) so you aren&rsquo;t as focused on the numbers of your run times.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Sneak it in:</strong>&nbsp;I work full-time, so about three times a week I would take a short, but hard, run at lunch (a &ldquo;runch&rdquo;), with intervals like 4x3-minute race-pace efforts with one-minute breaks.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/mg-9493-1546467181.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/483137_resized686534.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(407, 'The Ultimate Guide for Easy Meal Prepping', 'How to prep easy, affordable breakfasts, lunches, and dinners for your week. ', '<p><em>Guys, there&rsquo;s a secret to eating healthy, home-cooked meals that won&rsquo;t waste hours after work &mdash; and no, it&#39;s not investing in a personal chef. It&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.mealprephaven.com/blog-1/2015/9/21/meal-prepping-101-for-beginners\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">meal prepping</a>, or creating a few meals or dishes and portioning them out throughout the week. This can be as easy as stocking up on cottage cheese for breakfast, or as complicated as making a bunch of meals on Sunday and saving them for the rest of the week. Either way, it will save you time and money &mdash; and it&#39;ll ensure that you stick to a healthy diet.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;One of the biggest downfalls I see with clients regarding their compliance to their nutrition program is making poor nutrition decisions in the moment,&rdquo; says&nbsp;Men&rsquo;s Health&nbsp;nutrition advisor Mike Roussell, Ph.D. &ldquo;When you prep meals ahead of time, you don&rsquo;t need to make any decisions at meal time. All the work has already been done. You just need to eat.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Need help getting started? We&rsquo;ve outlined the basics and provided some tips to make it a bit less overwhelming.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a26041846/roman-reigns-hobbs-and-shaw/\\\"><img alt=\\\"roman reigns\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/screen-shot-2019-01-25-at-3-11-26-pm-1548447128.png?crop=1.00xw:0.549xh;0,0.0684xh&amp;resize=320:*\\\" /></a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>1</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a26041846/roman-reigns-hobbs-and-shaw/\\\">Roman Reigns Cast in &#39;Hobbs &amp; Shaw&#39;</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/fitness/a26040142/burpees-new-workout/\\\"><img alt=\\\"Man training in gym, jumping in mid air\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/man-training-in-gym-jumping-in-mid-air-royalty-free-image-961178276-1548439379.jpg?crop=0.849xw:0.637xh;0.0192xw,0.276xh&amp;resize=320:*\\\" /></a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>2</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/fitness/a26040142/burpees-new-workout/\\\">Get Fitter Faster With the New Burpee</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/style/g26024495/best-shaving-creams-gels/\\\"><img alt=\\\"image\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/harrys2-1548347581.jpg?crop=1.00xw:0.752xh;0,0&amp;resize=320:*\\\" /></a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>3</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/style/g26024495/best-shaving-creams-gels/\\\">The 10 Best Shaving Creams for Men</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a25632914/5-reasons-why-you-need-to-ditch-the-carbs-at-breakfast/\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fried eggs on the menu for breakfast\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/fried-eggs-on-the-menu-for-breakfast-royalty-free-image-511666438-1545336394.jpg?crop=1.00xw:0.752xh;0,0.0673xh&amp;resize=320:*\\\" /></a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>4</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a25632914/5-reasons-why-you-need-to-ditch-the-carbs-at-breakfast/\\\">5 Reasons to Start Your Day Without Carbs</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Created for&nbsp;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jimmy Dean</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/fitness/g26014893/best-rowing-machines/\\\"><img alt=\\\"image\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/rowing-1548283855.jpg?crop=1.00xw:0.753xh;0,0.0432xh&amp;resize=320:*\\\" /></a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>5</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/fitness/g26014893/best-rowing-machines/\\\">The Best Indoor Rowers for Your Home Gym</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1><em>The Ultimate Guide for Easy Meal Prepping</em></h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>How to prep easy, affordable breakfasts, lunches, and dinners for your week.&nbsp;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>BY&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/author/4710/marygrace-taylor/\\\">MARYGRACE TAYLOR</a>&nbsp;AND&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/author/219324/Melissa-Matthews/\\\">MELISSA MATTHEWS</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>NOV 2, 2018<img alt=\\\"Set of take away food boxes at white background\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/set-of-take-away-food-boxes-at-white-background-royalty-free-image-932207876-1541192410.jpg?crop=0.505xw:1.00xh;0.455xw,0&amp;resize=480:*\\\" /></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>GETTY IMAGESMILKOS</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Guys, there&rsquo;s a secret to eating healthy, home-cooked meals that won&rsquo;t waste hours after work &mdash; and no, it&#39;s not investing in a personal chef. It&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.mealprephaven.com/blog-1/2015/9/21/meal-prepping-101-for-beginners\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">meal prepping</a>, or creating a few meals or dishes and portioning them out throughout the week. This can be as easy as stocking up on cottage cheese for breakfast, or as complicated as making a bunch of meals on Sunday and saving them for the rest of the week. Either way, it will save you time and money &mdash; and it&#39;ll ensure that you stick to a healthy diet.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;One of the biggest downfalls I see with clients regarding their compliance to their nutrition program is making poor nutrition decisions in the moment,&rdquo; says&nbsp;Men&rsquo;s Health&nbsp;nutrition advisor Mike Roussell, Ph.D. &ldquo;When you prep meals ahead of time, you don&rsquo;t need to make any decisions at meal time. All the work has already been done. You just need to eat.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Need help getting started? We&rsquo;ve outlined the basics and provided some tips to make it a bit less overwhelming.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>1) Calculate how many meals you need.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Think about how many breakfasts, lunches, snacks and dinners you&rsquo;ll need throughout the week. Technically, if you want enough breakfast, lunches and dinners for the workweek, you would need 15 meals, but you don&#39;t have to cook 15 separate dishes. Instead, prepare a few large batches of meat and vegetables that can be used in various ways throughout the week.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Check out this downloadable template from&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.thekitchn.com/the-kitchns-meal-plan-template-252951\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">The Kitchn</a>&nbsp;to plan for the week. Or try one of our easy&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539506/steak-n-shrooms-one-pan-dinner/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">protein-packed</a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/g22552078/best-keto-breakfast-ideas/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">recipes</a>. And one additional tip: be sure to factor in things like dates and meals with clients. That way, you can plan more efficiently and avoid wasting food.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>2) Keep it simple.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you&rsquo;re new to cooking, Registered Dietitian and health coach at StrongerU, Jessica Bachman, PhD, MS-MPH, recommends staying away from recipes that require too many ingredients. Instead, &ldquo;think of a meal as a veggie, a protein and a starch,&rdquo; she says. So for instance, a quick dinner could be roasted pork loin, broccoli, and sweet potato.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>3) Utilize leftovers.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Bachman&rsquo;s clients often struggle with planning both lunch and dinner. &ldquo;Just choose one meal to start with. Then once you get a handle on that, start adding in more,&rdquo; she says. Plus, you can make extra for dinner and eat the leftovers for lunch. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s so much easier than trying to take a different meal for lunch every day,&rdquo; she explains</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>4) Opt for easy cooking methods.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Sure, you may love the grill marks on that chicken, but cooking on the grill or stove requires more attention. Bachman recommends using an oven or slow cooker, since you can throw food in for a designated amount of time and simply monitor its progress. Plus, it&rsquo;s easier to cook large batches of food with both of these methods</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>5) Rely on frozen foods.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>There&rsquo;s no need to prepare every single item on your plate. Instead of washing, cutting and steaming that side of broccoli, buy frozen vegetables instead. Additionally, many&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25526594\\\">frozen fruits and vegetables</a>, like broccoli, have just as many vitamins and minerals as their fresh counterparts.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>6) Keep breakfast simple.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Mornings can be hectic, which is why Bachman recommends having the same breakfast every day. Just chop up some fruit so it can be thrown in the blender for smoothies, or pair it with Greek yogurt for a change of pace.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>7) Have a go-to snack.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Similarly, Bachman advises choosing one snack, like pre-portioned nuts or a batch of hard-boiled eggs, that you can eat every day. That way, you won&#39;t have to hit up the vending machine when you&#39;re hit with the munchies.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>8) Get creative.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Eating chicken every night doesn&rsquo;t have to be boring. Bachman says she makes a big batch of shredded chicken every week and uses it for a variety of dishes, like salads or fajitas. She recommends having a variety of sauces and seasonings on-hand, such as barbeque, buffalo, etc., to make each meal feel unique.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>9) Buy budget-friendly staples.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>There&rsquo;s no need to spend money on organic, grass-fed beef if you can&rsquo;t afford it. There are plenty of affordable, filling and nutrient-dense foods like eggs, quinoa and sweet potatoes, according to Bachman. For example,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a23737566/how-much-protein-eggs/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">one large egg</a>&nbsp;has 6.3 grams of protein, is loaded with vitamins A, D, E, and K and will only set you back $2 for one dozen (<a href=\\\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/236852/retail-price-of-eggs-in-the-united-states/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">on average</a>). Bachman recommends whipping up a veggie-loaded cauliflower fried rice with eggs for a budget-conscious and well-balanced meal.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Other economical picks that have plenty of protein include canned tuna, beans and salmon. Keep them on-hand to pair with meal-prepped salads, veggies or whole wheat pasta dishes.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Bachman also recommends buying seasonally. Opt for brussels sprouts and broccoli when they&rsquo;re in season during the fall because prices will be lower. In winter, switch them out for turnips and winter squash.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>10) Write out your list and go shopping.</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>With your meals lined up, it&rsquo;s time to make a grocery list and head to the store. Try to do your big weekly shop on Saturday or early Sunday, so you have time to prep your ingredients before the work week begins. To get in and out as fast as possible, organize your grocery list by section (produce, meat, dairy, etc.).</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/set-of-take-away-food-boxes-at-white-background-royalty-free-image-932207876-1541192410.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/405067_resized58910.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(408, '5 Tiny Details That Make or Break Your Look', 'This is how you turn heads—in a good way', '<p>Getting dressed is one time it&rsquo;s OK to sweat the small stuff. Purposeful details add interest to your outfit, and show your boss (or lady friend) that you pick up on the little things. Here are five quick and cheap upgrades.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/tiebar-details-1505219969.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/335828_resized914858.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(409, 'The 15 Best Anti-Aging Products for Men', 'Get rid of those wrinkles and fine lines.', '<p><em>Everyone ages differently, and some guys just seem to &quot;age better&quot; than others. While habits like a healthy diet and getting enough sleep can help you age well, a good skincare routine that includes some anti-aging products can do wonders for things like fine lines, crow&#39;s feet and circles. It&#39;s all in the active ingredients, whether its retinol, vitamin C or other antioxidants.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>We&#39;ve rounded up some of the best anti-aging products for your face, hands and body. See the results for yourself!</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/615138_resized780802.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(410, 'The 10-Minute Transformation', '     ', '<h2>Every second is a lung-busting, sweat-pouring challenge. No time wasted, no room for excuses</h2>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(411, 'Meghan Markle Says Her 20s Were \'Brutal\' Compared to Her 30s', '    ', '<p>Meghan Markle has long abandoned her lifestyle site&nbsp;<em>The Tig</em>, where occasionally she&#39;d blog about her experiences as a working actress and young woman in her early thirties.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>But&nbsp;<em><a href=\\\"https://www.express.co.uk/news/royal/1077422/meghan-markle-news-the-tig-meghan-markle-brutal-teenage-years-happiness\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Express</a>&nbsp;</em>and&nbsp;<em><a href=\\\"https://people.com/royals/meghan-markle-2014-birthday-message/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">People</a>&nbsp;</em>dug up one of her personal blog posts, where Meghan discussed her struggles in her teens and early twenties while she was trying to figure herself out&mdash;and why, quite frankly, those years weren&#39;t her greatest, something many women can relate to.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meghan was candid&nbsp;in the 2014 post published on her thirty-third birthday: &quot;I am 33 years old today. And I am happy,&quot; she started it. &quot;And I say that so plainly because, well&hellip; it takes time. To be happy. To figure out how to be kind to yourself. To not just choose that happiness, but to feel it.&quot;Then she described her coming into adulthood. &ldquo;My 20s were brutal&mdash;a constant battle with myself, judging my weight, my style, my desire to be as cool/as hip/as smart/as &lsquo;whatever&rsquo; as everyone else. My teens were even worse&mdash;grappling with how to fit in, and what that even meant. My high school had cliques: the black girls and white girls, the Filipino and the Latina girls. Being biracial, I fell somewhere in between. I must have been about 24 when a casting director looked at me during an audition and said, &lsquo;You need to know that you&rsquo;re enough. Less makeup, more Meghan.&rsquo;&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Then, she poignantly told her readers the lesson she learned: to look within to find value, not to any boyfriend, job, or whatever else. &ldquo;You need to know that you&rsquo;re enough,&quot; she wrote. &quot;A mantra that has now engrained itself so deeply within me that not a day goes by without hearing it chime in my head. That five pounds lost won&rsquo;t make you happier, that more makeup won&rsquo;t make you prettier, that the now iconic saying from Jerry Maguire&mdash;&lsquo;You complete me&rsquo;&mdash;frankly, isn&rsquo;t true. You are complete with or without a partner. You are enough just as you are.&rdquo;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Makes you wish the royal family would let Meghan blog still but alas, life isn&#39;t&nbsp;<em>A Christmas Prince</em><em>.</em></p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/gettyimages-1048991414.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/277170_resized689407.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(412, 'Demi Lovato Offers Supportive Message To Bebe Rexha Over Inclusive Fashion', 'Rexha said design houses wouldn\'t dress her for being \"too big.\"', '<p><em>Singer-actress Demi Lovato has always been a body-positive advocate, and even recently took to Instagram to voice her criticism of fat-shaming. And so it&#39;s only natural that she would have some positive words in support of Bebe Rexha, who&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.marieclaire.com/culture/a25989812/bebe-rexha-designer-grammys-dress-size-8-snub/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">took the fashion industry to task in an Instagram video</a>, saying she was &quot;too big&quot; for a number of design houses to dress her for the Grammys. In the Instagram comments and first spotted by&nbsp;People,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://people.com/style/demi-lovato-praises-bebe-rexha-for-blasting-designers/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Lovato praised Rexha for taking a stand</a>.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>In the video, Rexha explained, &quot;I had my team hit out a lot of designers, and a lot of them do not want to dress me because I&rsquo;m too big. Literally, like, I&rsquo;m too big.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&quot;If a size 6/8 is too big, then I don&rsquo;t know what to tell you,&quot; she said. &quot;Then I don&rsquo;t want to wear your f&mdash;king dresses because that&rsquo;s crazy &lsquo;cause you&rsquo;re saying that all the women in the world that are a size 8 and up are not beautiful and they cannot wear your dresses.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Lovato immediately rushed to Rexha&#39;s defense. &quot;F&mdash;king preach!&quot; the singer commented. &quot;Love this and you for speaking your mind and using your voice!!!&quot; she Adedd</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Earlier this month,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.marieclaire.com/celebrity/a25756325/demi-lovato-fat-shaming-instagram-ad/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Lovato spotted an ad for&nbsp;Game of Sultans</a>&nbsp;calling an average weight woman &quot;obese&quot; and comparing her to a thinner, &quot;pretty&quot; woman. &quot;Why is this fat shaming bullsh*t on my feed?&quot; she asked. &quot;You can be &#39;pretty&#39; at any weight.&quot; The game company apologized and took the ad down.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Meanwhile, Rexha has received&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://people.com/style/bebe-rexha-dress-offers-2019-grammy-awards/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">a number of offers to dress her for the Grammys</a>. So it sounds like the vocal comments that the two singers have made are helping to, slowly, make a difference in the industry.</em></p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2022-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/gettyimages-970362522-1548326713.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/228526_resized777721.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(413, 'Will a Vitamin IV Drip Actually Cure Your Hangover or Cold?', '    ', '<p>With a new diet or wellness hack cropping up on a weekly basis, the world of health fads never sleeps. Propelled by celebrity endorsements and anecdotal praise, everything from oxygen bars to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/health/a23134431/chrissy-teigen-placenta-postpartum-depression/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">placenta pills</a>&nbsp;have all enjoyed some time in the limelight. But one of the latest crazes to hit the health scene is IV vitamin drip therapy.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>IV vitamin therapy, also known as vitamin IV drip and IV vitamin drip therapy, involves hooking up to an IV bag to receive a vitamins and minerals. Clinics offering these treatments are popping up across the country, as people are seeking this therapy in hopes of fighting off illness, obtaining more radiant skin,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/life/a22789047/hangover-cures/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">beating a hangover</a>, or other purported benefits.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>But whether these claims have any merit is a matter of debate. We spoke with two doctors to learn more about who might benefit from IV vitamin therapy&mdash;and how&mdash;plus whether there are any drawbacks or risks to having it.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Does IV vitamin therapy work?</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>IV vitamin clinics often make a number of claims about the benefits of these therapies, suggesting that they might help with&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/g20474000/7-foods-that-stop-hair-loss/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hair</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/beauty/skin-care/g25249917/anti-aging-foods-every-decade/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">skin health</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/healthy-eating/a20503059/power-foods-that-boost-immunity/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">boost immunity</a>, or cure a hangover. But for the most part, experts say the evidence to support these claims are scant.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&ldquo;I do not know of any convincing evidence that, for example, an IV drip of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/g20734052/zinc-deficiency-symptoms/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">zinc</a>, B12, C, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/g20105121/magnesium-deficiency-symptoms/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">magnesium</a>&nbsp;will cure colds and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.prevention.com/health/health-conditions/g25996639/common-flu-myths-debunked/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">flu</a>,&rdquo; says&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.detar.com/find-a-doctor/ontai-sidney-md-9320\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Sidney C. Ontai</a>, MD, a family medicine doctor and program director at Texas A&amp;M University&rsquo;s DeTar Family Medicine Residency.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On the other hand,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://nyulangone.org/doctors/1285860569/albert-ahn\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Albert Ahn</a>, MD, an internal medicine physician and clinical instructor of medicine at NYU Langone Health, says that IV vitamin drips might provide two clear-cut benefits. For one, IV vitamin therapy ensures that vitamins and minerals are absorbed faster than they would be via oral consumption or supplementation.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/pieces-of-fresh-fruit-inside-of-intravenous-high-res-stock-photography-717157837-1548268054.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/454784_resized188239.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(414, 'There\'s A Very Specific Reason Why The Royals Don\'t Wear Seat Belts', 'It\'s for their...safety?', '<p>Ever since&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/a25936821/prince-philip-car-accident-injured-safe/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Prince Philip had his car accident</a>, there&#39;s been a lot of ~chatter~ about the fact that the royal family often don&#39;t wear seat belts. In fact,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://people.com/royals/queen-elizabeth-drives-without-seatbelt-after-prince-philip-crash/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Queen Elizabeth was seen driving sans seat belt</a>&nbsp;in the wake of Philip&#39;s accident, which is pretty, uh...questionable.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The thing is, the royal fam actually has a good-<em>ish</em>&nbsp;reason for being so unsafe. And ironically that reason has to do with their own personal safety. Speaking to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.hellomagazine.com/royalty/2019012366953/protection-officer-explains-royals-not-wearing-seatbelts/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><em>Hello Magazine</em></a>, former royal protection officer Simon Morgan explained that sometimes royals don&#39;t wear seat belts in order to escape quickly in an emergency.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;There are always anomalies,&quot; Morgan said. &quot;In the threat and risk matrix it&#39;s a matter of looking at each individual situation to decide what is the best way of achieving what needs to be achieved. For example, considering that a quick entry or exit to a vehicle is easier when people aren&#39;t strapped into seat belts.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>He added, &quot;Also, what is significant about this event or situation? Is an individual&#39;s look and appearance important? And also an individual&#39;s choice. Protection is a very unique area of policing and there are a lot grey areas, but you are always judging each situation to weigh up the risks and threats with the outcomes you are trying to achieve.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Guess that settles that! But for what it&#39;s worth, the younger royals know whattup:</p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/gettyimages-506228894-1548331665.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/591978_resized118799.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(415, 'This Keto-Friendly Breakfast Helped One Woman Lose 100 Pounds', 'Best part: You can make it in 90 seconds!', '<p><em>One day in early 2017, life changed forever for Elena Juarez. Her daughter had come home from school with a note from the nurse, asking if her and her mother had ever been tested for diabetes. The Texas native&mdash;then weighing 256 pounds&mdash;was shook. She knew it was time to make a permanent change in her household for the betterment of her and her family&rsquo;s health.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>carbs and high in fat, following a keto lifestyle felt accessible for the mother of two. And soon enough, the weight started to come off more rapidly.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s been nearly two years, and I&rsquo;m now down 108 pounds. I can&rsquo;t even imagine going back to the place where I was,&rdquo; Juarez tells Women&rsquo;s Health. &ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t feel comfortable then. Adopting the keto diet helped me gain control over food. It&rsquo;s the only diet that&rsquo;s ever made me feel that way. I can eat what I want, feel satisfied, and most importantly, I&rsquo;m comfortable in my body. Finally&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>6 a.m. Her alarm starts blaring</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;My alarm goes off around 6 a.m., and the first thing I do is get in the shower and blow-dry my hair. Then, I&rsquo;m immediately waking up my girls and getting them going so we can get ready for school and the day.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>7 a.m. Time to prep the girls&rsquo; lunches</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;They&rsquo;re totally different in what they like to eat, but they both love to take a piece of fruit along with whatever sandwich, flatbread, or wrap I make them. We&rsquo;re all big on strawberries, raspberries, and blackberries, which is great for me because they&#39;re low in carbs and high in fiber.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>7:45 a.m. School drop-off with a side of caffeine</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;Most days, I&rsquo;m just getting the girls to school at the cut-off time. Then, I&rsquo;m off to grab my coffee, because Lord knows I need it. I&rsquo;ll get it black, hot, or iced depending on what the weather looks like.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Once I get to the office, that&rsquo;s when I put in my creamer. Lately, I&rsquo;ve been doing a mix of heavy cream and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01F2PYV20/?tag=womenshealth-auto-20&amp;ascsubtag=[artid|2140.a.25683896[src|socialflowFBWH[ch|[lt|\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Nut Pods creamer</a>, which cuts the calories in half. I record everything I eat and drink in the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.carbmanager.com/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Carb Manager App</a>. It calculates net carbs for me and leaves the math out (subtracting fiber and sugar alcohols from total carbs). It&rsquo;s super easy to use. So I type my coffee in before heading to the office where I settle in for the day and grab breakfast.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>8:00 a.m. Breakfast</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;This always changes. Some days, I get to it before we leave the house and other days, I don&#39;t eat until I get to the office. When I&rsquo;m pressed for time, I&#39;ll reach for a cup of berries and a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576255&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fad.doubleclick.net%2Fddm%2Fclk%2F430031237%3B232305514%3Bj&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.womenshealthmag.com%2Fweight-loss%2Fa25683896%2Fketo-friendly-breakfast-weight-loss%2F\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Jimmy Dean Egg&#39;wich</a>. It has two frittatas instead of bread, so it&#39;s low-carb and keto-friendly. Plus, it&#39;s literally ready to eat in 90 seconds! This is a really quick, satisfying way to start my day.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>9:00 a.m. She connects with her husband</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;We&rsquo;re together like 24/7. It&rsquo;s awesome. People will ask how Edson and I do it. It just works. We know how to separate our business relationship with our home relationship. He&rsquo;s my number one fan and biggest supporter. We&rsquo;ll even workout together (we love kickboxing), but that&rsquo;s always at night.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/2-010419-whxjimmydean-lede-horizontal-r1-1-1546621627.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/722078_resized912795.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(416, 'Prince William Says Celebrities Didn\'t Want to Work with His Mental Health Campaign', '\"Not one person wanted to be involved\" when he started the Heads Together initiative, he says.', '<p><em>Prince William, Kate Middleton, and Prince Harry have been tackling the stigma of mental health through their campaign,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.royal.uk/launch-headstogether-campaign-0\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Heads Together</a>, for a few years now. Although the initiative has gained momentum across the U.K. since it launched in May 2016, it had rough beginnings. The Duke of Cambridge revealed that they struggled to get a celebrity to publicly support the cause because it was mental health-related.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&quot;What was very interesting from when we set up the campaign was that not one celebrity wanted to join us,&quot; he said during a panel at the World Economic forum in Davos, Switzerland yesterday. &quot;Not one person wanted to be involved in the mental health campaign, Heads Together.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>The Duke of Cambridge continued, &quot;We went out to a lot of people and nobody, before we started, was interested in being a part of Heads Together&mdash;because it was mental health. That was two years, three years ago. You know, and that was a big deal.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>However, people&#39;s minds changed once they were able to understand the work Heads Together was putting out. William said: &quot;Then obviously, once we started to get the ball rolling, once we started showing people what we were going to do, people realized that Catherine, Harry, and I put our necks on the line here, that maybe actually it was okay we could join, then some very brave people came forward, from celebrities and from normal people who decided this was really important, and they bravely took on the task of speaking out about mental health.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/the-duke-and-duchess-of-cambridge-and-prince-harry-are-news-photo-523671780-1548340538.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/607484_resized459220.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(417, 'Jenna Jameson Says She Feared Postpartum Weight Loss Before Keto Diet', '\"I prayed for breast feeding to give me an easy way out. It didn\'t.\"', '<p><em>Pregnancy can throw even the most confident woman for a loop. Hair starts growing in weird places, you&rsquo;re stuck wearing granny pants with elastic waistbands, and you wonder if your body will ever feel like your own again.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jenna Jameson knows the feeling all too well&mdash;and she just opened up about it in a new&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BtCNBDTBMbA/\\\">Instagram</a>&nbsp;post.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&quot;I was just going through my images and I came across these beautiful pregnancy pics we took in Palm Springs,&quot; she captioned a &quot;before&quot; photo of herself (while pregnant) poolside in a bikini alongside an &quot;after&quot; photo of herself now. &quot;I was 38 weeks pregnant and felt like a truck. But I&rsquo;ve never felt more beautiful than when I was with child.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jenna said she remembers feeling &quot;so frightened&quot; to think about what would happen after her daughter was born: &quot;I couldn&rsquo;t blame being heavy on the pregnancy,&quot; she said. And as for her attempts at weight loss after pregnancy? &quot;I prayed for breastfeeding to give me an easy way out. It didn&rsquo;t. I was scared my belly would sag down and never tighten.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jenna acknowledges that it &quot;sounds vain&quot; but says she thinks every mom silently worries about this. &quot;Yes we love our babies and we would do it over again in a second, but we sacrifice so much!&quot; she continued. &quot;This after picture shows that we can do it!&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jenna eventually lost 80 pounds on the keto diet&mdash;and she talks about her journey often. She shares things like what she&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.womenshealthmag.com/weight-loss/a22774609/jenna-jameson-keto-meal-plan/\\\">eats on a daily basis</a>&nbsp;(eggs with cheese and avocado for breakfast, arugula salad with meat for lunch, and nuts or cottage cheese for a snack) and her&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.womenshealthmag.com/weight-loss/g25460169/jenna-jameson-keto-diet-trader-joes/\\\">Trader Joe&rsquo;s shopping list</a>.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Jenna stressed in her latest post that postpartum weight loss can be a challenge, but she&rsquo;s living proof that it can happen. &quot;We can regain ourselves,&quot; she wrote. &quot;We can do it without surgery (not that I&rsquo;m against surgery). So to all of you sweet pregnant mamas out there or you newly postpartum mamas... I see you.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2022-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/Capture.JPG', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/750410_resized384856.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(418, 'The 12 Best Eucalyptus Oil Benefits For Your Hair, Skin, and More', 'Guys, this essential oil does everything.', '<p><em>Congested? Sore? Anxious? There&rsquo;s an essential oil for that.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Essential oils may seem like a buzzy trend in the beauty and wellness space, but there&rsquo;s no denying the extensive benefits found in age-old plant extracts&mdash;especially eucalyptus oil.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Eucalyptus oil can help clear your sinuses, relieve sore muscles, and combat stress. But before you slather it all over your entire body,&nbsp;<strong>let&rsquo;s break down what it is and how to use it safely and effectively</strong>.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>What is eucalyptus oil?</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Eucalyptus oil comes from the oval-shaped leaves of the eucalyptus tree, which is native to Australia. The leaves are dried, crushed, and distilled to release the powerful essential oil, says Amy Galper, co-founder of the National Association of Holistic Aromatherapy.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>The main ingredient is cineole (also known as eucalyptol), which is known for its anti-inflammatory, analgesic, and aromatic properties. Australian Aboriginals used eucalyptus as a natural remedy against wounds, infections, aches, and colds.</em></p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/eucalyptus-essential-oil-1548374423 (1).jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/744260_resized987561.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(419, 'How to Cope if You Hate Your Boss', 'Because avoiding them is sadly not an option.', '<p>There are two facts every employee should know: Bad managers exist. And you&rsquo;re probably going to have one at some point in your career. Fortunately, there are ways to cope if you hate your boss that don&#39;t involve venting on social media or doing anything that will sabotage your chances of further success at the company. Here&#39;s how to make it through the workday if you&#39;re stuck with one exceptionally sour apple.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>First, while easier said than done, try to talk to your boss.</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This one may seem like a no-brainer but you&rsquo;d be amazed how many people never actually try sitting down to discuss their issues, says Peter Holmes, Esq, an attorney specializing in employment law and human resources at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.wirehouse-es.com/\\\">Wirehouse Employer Services</a>.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&ldquo;Find a time to have a calm, relaxed conversation with your boss to express your feelings, and perhaps raise questions over events that upset you,&rdquo; he says. You may discover that your boss didn&rsquo;t realize how their actions were affecting you or that you were even upset.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Again, this may be difficult&mdash;especially if you can&#39;t exactly stand the person, but &ldquo;Having an organized, informal chat with your manager can result in breaking the ice, resolving the issues in a mature way, and be surprisingly productive if conducted in the right tone and manner,&rdquo; Holmes explains.</p>\\r\\n', 20, 84, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-10', './images/newsCms/Data/gettyimages-1002930806.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/907012_resized892596.jpg', 0, 'True');
