(420, '9 Ways to Get Rid of a Cold Sore Fast', 'There’s no cure for mouth sores, but you can make them disappear more quickly', '<p><em>If you&#39;ve had cold sores before, that tingling feeling in your lip usually only means one thing: a new bunch of blisters is set to erupt.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Cold sores are usually caused by herpes simplex virus type 1, a strain closely related to the type 2 bug responsible for causing genital blisters spread by sexual contact. Cold sores on the lips are mostly spread through casual skin-to-skin contact, but&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/sex/5-oral-sex-moves-youve-never-tried\\\">oral sex</a>can spread genital herpes to the mouth.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/style/spots-as-an-adult-how-to-treat-them\\\">(Related: Spots as an adult and how to treat them)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Cold sores are uncomfortable and can also be unsightly. The good thing is that they&rsquo;ll usually clear up on their own in two to four weeks. The not-so-swell part? You&rsquo;ll be sporting some red, oozing, and then crusting blisters on your mouth until then.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Once you pick up the cold sore virus, it sits dormant in your nerve cells until a trigger &ndash; say, stress, an illness, or hormone &ndash; prompts it to rear its ugly head again. So the best way to avoid an outbreak is to reduce your exposure to certain triggers. If you already have a cold sore, don&rsquo;t worry &ndash; we&#39;ve got you covered. Follow these tips below to send your cold sore packing.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/sex/are-the-spots-on-your-penis-really-dangerous\\\">(Related: Are the spots on your penis really dangerous?)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>1. Catch it early</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Cold sores aren&rsquo;t a wait-and-see condition: early diagnosis is the best way to put the brakes on their arrival.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;You can actually keep them from breaking out, or perhaps keep them from breaking out as badly as they otherwise would,&rdquo; says Bruce Robinson, M.D., a dermatologist in private practice in New York City and clinical instructor of dermatology at Lenox Hill Hospital.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/style/how-to-stop-sweating-after-your-gym-session-mag\\\">(Related: How to stop sweating after your gym session)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Be on the lookout for what the docs call the &ldquo;prodromal stage,&rdquo; including symptoms like tingling, itching, inflammation, or soreness in areas where the sores will later break out. If you feel anything funny, call your doc to start treatment</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>2. Try an antiviral</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Topical over-the-counter meds don&rsquo;t work as well as prescription antivirals, says Robinson. Over-the-counter creams may provide relief from the tingling and burning, but they aren&rsquo;t the best option if you want sores gone fast.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>The best way to treat cold sores is to start treatment early in that prodromal stage, with a prescription oral antiviral medication like valacyclovir (which you probably know as Valtrex), says Lorraine Young, M.D., co-chief of dermatology clinical services at UCLA.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/style/the-mh-guide-to-ingrowing-hair\\\">(Related: How to spot and treat ingrown hairs)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>A common regimen is to take 2,000 milligrams in the morning and again later on in the day. This &quot;decreases the virus from replicating, so then it will help it to heal faster,&rdquo; says Young. Preventing the virus from replicating prevents it from going through its normal course. The result? It can reduce the time it takes your blisters to heal&mdash;or even prevent them from appearing in the first place.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>3. Add a steroid cream</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If your doctor prescribes oral antiviral meds, you might benefit from including a topical steroid cream treatment too, says Young.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>This can help reduce the inflammation associated with the sores, which can make the pain, redness, and irritation feel a little bit better.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Important note: steroid creams are only an option if you&rsquo;re on the antiviral drugs. That&rsquo;s because steroids decrease your body&rsquo;s ability to fight infections.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;If you just did the cream without viral therapy, you would be feeding the cold sore infection,&rdquo; says Young. &ldquo;But if you&rsquo;re on the antiviral medicines, that could help decrease the symptoms.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>4. Make your own cold sore solution</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Robinson advises making a solution with Domeboro, a powder used to help with skin irritation. Available at the drugstore, dissolve the tablets or packet of the powder in about 12 to 16 ounces of water. You&rsquo;ll notice some gunk at the bottom of the glass &ndash; that&rsquo;s okay.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Then dunk a thin cloth, like a handkerchief or pillowcase, into the glass. Wring it out and lay it on the blistering area for about 15 to 30 minutes. Repeat two to three times a day until the sores dry out. Be sure to make a new batch of the solution each time.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;It sucks the moisture and water out of the blister,&rdquo; says Robinson. &ldquo;I can get someone who has an outbreak to scab within 3 days using that &ndash; which otherwise might take a week to 10 days.&rdquo;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/style/whats-the-best-way-to-shave-your-chest\\\">(Related: This is the best way to shave your chest)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Once it&rsquo;s dry, stop the soaks and keep the area moist with a topical antibiotic ointment like Neosporin. This helps prevent secondary bacterial infection and aids the healing process.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>5. Use cold compresses</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Reduce swelling and irritation with a cool, wet towel. The American Academy of Dermatology recommends using a cold compress for 5 to 10 minutes several times a day while you&#39;re waiting for blisters to heal. Avoiding particularly acidic foods like tomatoes and oranges helps keep irritation to a minimum, too.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em>6. Don&#39;t touch them &ndash; ever</em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Those red cold sore blisters are packed with fluid, making them prime for popping. Don&rsquo;t do it.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;People pick at anything on their skin, so it can be tempting to do that,&rdquo; says Young. &ldquo;But anytime you do that, it can get secondarily infected.&rdquo; And that&rsquo;s bad news: Bacterial infections can make the sores stick around longer, and picking at a bad infection can lead to scarring.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>7. Identify your triggers</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you&#39;re prone to cold sores, the virus that&rsquo;s hibernating in your cells is more likely to emerge when you&rsquo;re stressed out, sick, or if your skin is dry.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Sun is also a major factor that can set off an outbreak.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;Our immune system is compromised to some degree by ultraviolet light,&rdquo; says Robinson. This means you&rsquo;re less likely to fight off infections.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Your move? Slather on sunscreen with an SPF of at least 30 before going outside. And don&rsquo;t forget to slap on some Chapstick as well.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>8. Use aloe vera</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>While it won&#39;t zap cold sores overnight, aloe vera has been found to reduce the pain associated with cold sores. It also contains vitamins A, C, and E, which may help to expedite the healing process.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>9. Avoid acidic or spicy foods</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>While you&#39;re recovering from a cold sore, it&#39;s probably best to lay off the hot sauce for a while. Try to avoid hot and spicy foods, particularly if your sores are still open and haven&#39;t scabbed over yet. The same goes for acidic foods, like pineapple, tomatoes, and citrus fruit.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>A version of this article originally appeared on<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a19540654/cold-sore-treatment/\\\">&nbsp;MensHealth.com</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>From:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a19540654/cold-sore-treatment/\\\">Men&#39;s Health US</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-30', './images/newsCms/Data/coldsores.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/423397_resized462658.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(421, '5 easy ways to look immediately more stylish', 'An almost obvious list that will smarten you up (and cost nothing)', '<p><em>These five tips for looking smarter right away might sound obvious but they are often the overlooked details that other people notice. Polish your shoes, press your clothes and tuck your shirt in- these are the small changes that will make a big difference.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Tonal dressing means wearing different shades of one colour all at once. It&rsquo;s a simple way of avoiding the pitfalls of mismatching colours and a shortcut to looking well turned out with very little thought. The obvious choice is to wear all black but all navy or grey will work just as well. The secret is to wear different textures so that you don&rsquo;t look like a pantone chart. Need an example? Dark blue denim jeans worn with a navy crew neck T-shirt and a navy overcoat will suit pretty much everyone.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>2.&nbsp;As simple as this sounds, ironing out your clothes will immediately make a difference to how they look and fit. Apart from suggesting to the wider world that you are a fully functioning adult, ironing can help restore the shape of seams and fabric that can warp when drying. Make life easier for yourself by using a bottle of water to spray the clothes with first, and turn your iron up high.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>3.There was a time when wearing one coat at a time was enough. That&rsquo;s fine if you&rsquo;re a fan of a down-filled parker, less so if you favour a colder, wool overcoat. To compensate, those in the wool camp are adding jackets underneath and the result is both stylistically pleasing and easily achieved. A denim jacket worn under an overcoat should do the trick.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>4.You wouldn&rsquo;t leave the house with a dusty, mud spattered pair of trousers on and the same should apply to your shoes. If you&rsquo;re in a rush, a wipe with a damp cloth to remove sitting dirt, followed by a once over with a dry cloth to bring out the shine in the leather will work wonders. Incidentally, as any soldier worth his rank will tell you, the best way to shine leather is with a balled-up pair of nylon tights.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>5.Tucking your T-shirt in is a simple way of breaking up your body into two well defined sections and at the same time making your legs look longer.&nbsp;<strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/style/your-one-essential-styling-tip-for-winter\\\">We expand on the idea here</a></strong>&nbsp;but in the meantime, choose a T-shirt with enough length in the body to stay tucked in, and suitable trousers to do it with. Tucking a t-shirt into jeans is a bit &#39;dad&#39; so try chinos, sweatpants or tailored trousers.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-23', './images/newsCms/Data/immeidatley_more_stylish.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/442479_resized724651.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(422, 'Barbell rollout', 'How to perform the barbell rollout with perfect form', '<h2><em>About this exercise</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n	<li><em><strong>Muscles Worked:&nbsp;</strong>Abs, Back, Shoulders</em></li>\\r\\n	<li><em><strong>Difficulty:&nbsp;</strong>Hard</em></li>\\r\\n	<li><em><strong>Equipment needed:&nbsp;</strong>Barbell</em></li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Load a barbell with 5kg plates and grab the bar with an overhand, shoulder-width grip. Position your shoulders directly over the barbell and slowly roll the bar forwards. Pause, then reverse the move.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-30', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(423, '4 Ways to Tell If You\'re Cheating Yourself During Workouts', 'You\'re basically lying to yourself', '<p><em>Everyone wants to be the guy who gets through reps at lightning speed and is the first to finish an&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/watch-the-british-armys-fat-torching-amrap-workout\\\">AMRAP during HIIT class.</a>&nbsp;But if you&rsquo;re taking shortcuts during your workout, the only person you&#39;re cheating is yourself. Don&rsquo;t believe us? Take a look at your arms: you&#39;re probably not bulking up as fast as you could be. You also might be practising bad form, which can easily put you at risk of injury.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/get-big/four-biggest-exercise-form-mistakes\\\">(Related: The 4 most common form mistakes)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you are taking shortcuts during your workouts, don&rsquo;t worry &mdash; you&rsquo;re not the only one. In fact,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/watch-the-mistakes-you-keep-making-at-the-gym\\\">there are a few workout mistakes that people tend to make in an attempt to get through their workout</a>&nbsp;fast or with minimal effort. We asked a few trainers to tell us about the most common workout shortcuts, so you know what to avoid in the future and can start seeing some serious gains.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>1. Not fully extending</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you&rsquo;re not lowering your chest fully to the ground during push-ups, you&rsquo;re taking the easy way out. &ldquo;Men want to appear powerful and often quickly descend and lower their pelvis to the floor instead of their chest, which is technically cheating,&rdquo; says Rebecca Gahan, C.P.T, the owner and founder of Kick@55 Fitness, a HIIT studio in Chicago.Instead, &ldquo;your hands should be positioned outside of your shoulders, with your body in plank position. Contract your arms and descend your chest to ground,&rdquo; she says.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>2. Not dropping low enough in your squats</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;People often don&rsquo;t descend down enough into the squat (to really activate those glutes and thighs) and simply jump up too quickly in attempts to power through them,&rdquo; Gahan says. Instead, go deep down in the squat, and ascend into a standing position as you jump into the air, she says.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>3. Going too fast or too slow</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Certain moves require slowing down for you to truly reap those muscle-firing rewards. For instance, for stationary lunges, &ldquo;many clients pulse quickly up and down as a way to get through a set,&rdquo; says Gahan. But that doesn&rsquo;t let them really activate those muscles in the legs and strengthen them over time.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/blogs/be-your-own-personal-trainer/be-your-own-personal-trainer-tempo-blog\\\">(Related: This is how fast you really should be lifting)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Instead, &ldquo;legs should be positioned in an upside-down L, 90-degree angle. You should descend until the knee almost touches the ground, and then ascend to a full standing position,&rdquo; she says. It&rsquo;s okay if it&rsquo;s a bit slower as long as your form is good.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>On the other hand, moves like mountain climbers, which are aimed at cardio than building strength, should be done slightly faster. &ldquo;With mountain climbers, clients often bring the knee to mid-chest and slow down the movement. But this is problematic, as it barely works the core and minimises cardio benefit,&rdquo; Gahan says. Instead, &ldquo;knees should shoot up to the chin, so that it barely misses. And, you should switch legs in one swift motion, with 2 reps per second, ideally,&rdquo; she adds</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>4. Slouching or arching your back</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you&rsquo;re arching, slouching, or just putting pressure on your back, you&rsquo;re not only jeopardising your progress, but you&rsquo;re also at risk for injury, explains Todd Nief, owner and founder of South Loop Strength &amp; Conditioning.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/blogs/maximize-every-exercise/how-to-do-the-perfect-plank\\\">(Related: Get more from the plank)</a></strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>This is especially common with planks. &ldquo;The plank is one of the better movements for developing anterior core strength, which can counterbalance a tendency toward excessive extension and arching of the lower back. However, many people allow their bodies to sag and arch, which is completely counterproductive.&rdquo; The key to a good plank is holding your back &ldquo;long and straight,&rdquo; even if it&rsquo;s for a shorter period of time</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(424, 'What Body Fat Percentage Should I Be to See Abs?', 'Getting a six-pack can be an uphill struggle, but you\'re closer than you think', '<p><em>Getting to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/the-best-way-to-get-to-single-digit-body-fat\\\">single-digit body fat</a>&nbsp;is often treated as a badge of honour among lifting circles. A direct result of diligent training and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/food-nutrition/\\\">precise nutrition</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/healthy/what-body-fat-percentage-should-i-be\\\">losing body fat</a>&nbsp;and getting your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/abs-workout/six-principles-of-six-pack-eating-146052\\\">six-pack</a>&nbsp;to show can be an venture that takes months (often years) to achieve.At this point, you&rsquo;re likely to know that you can&rsquo;t &#39;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/burn-fat/can-i-target-my-fat-loss\\\">target&#39; or spot-reduce fat</a>. Nor can you out-train a bad diet consisting of takeaways,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/food-nutrition/working-out-and-beer\\\">post-work pints</a>&nbsp;and sugary treats with a handful of lethargic gym sessions. To get a six-pack, you have to commit. Hard. But handily enough, you may be closer than you think. Below, we take you through six examples of a typical male physique to help you identify how close you are to getting those coveted&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/abs-workout/home-dumbbell-workout-six-pack-three-weeks\\\">six-pack abs</a>.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>30% Body Fat</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>For men aged 20-39, anything above 25 per cent body fat is classed as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/the-truth-about-obesity\\\">obese</a>. For men 40-years-old and above, it&#39;s 28 per cent. Generally considered to be excessive for men and women, 30 per cent body fat makes puts you in the &#39;at risk stage&#39;, which can lead to heart disease and cardiovascular issues.But what about BMI? Unless you&rsquo;re a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/this-pro-bodybuilder-gives-you-his-best-muscle-building-advice\\\">bodybuilder</a>&nbsp;or an athlete &mdash; maybe both &mdash; a high BMI usually correlates with a high percentage of body fat, so consult your GP to get an accurate reading. Needless to say, there are no&nbsp;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>25% Body Fat</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Again, this is the milestone to identifying whether or not you currently have an unhealthy physique. Not as dangerous at the aforementioned, men with around 25 per cent body fat are still carrying significant excess weight, albeit likely to be carrying an acceptable amount of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/exercise/boost-your-testosterone-with-just-4-moves\\\">muscle mass</a>, too.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Generally, a man with 25 per cent body fat will still look overweight, as the muscle beneath will be covered in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/burn-fat/fast-weight-loss-workout\\\">subcutaneous fat</a>.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>20% Body Fat</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>This is when things start to look a little more promising. In this bracket, men are likely to look a little&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/how-to-pack-on-muscle-if-youre-genetically-skinny\\\">&lsquo;skinny fat&rsquo;</a>&nbsp;&mdash; a result of a poor muscle-to-body-fat ratio &mdash; and a little softer.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Don&rsquo;t be disheartened, as any body fat percentage up to 20 per cent is considered healthy and will help stave off diseases that are associated with higher levels of body fat.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>15% Body Fat</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>In a word &ndash; lean. Or at least, starting to look lean. Somewhere between&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workout/the-best-joe-wicks-body-coach-workouts-for-men\\\">Joe Wicks</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/why-dehydrating-your-body-to-look-good-is-dangerous\\\">Wolverine</a>, maybe.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>At around 15 per cent body fat, men will tend to start seeing&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/fast/one-move-full-body-workout\\\">muscular shape and definition</a>, while noticing changes in body composition and fat stores. Your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/4-moves-to-give-you-huge-arms\\\">arms</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workout/7-best-exercises-for-bigger-shoulders-fast\\\">shoulders</a>&nbsp;are more vascular too. You&rsquo;re now on-track for&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/10-minute-six-pack-workout\\\">a six-pack.</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>15% Body Fat</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>In a word &ndash; lean. Or at least, starting to look lean. Somewhere between&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workout/the-best-joe-wicks-body-coach-workouts-for-men\\\">Joe Wicks</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/why-dehydrating-your-body-to-look-good-is-dangerous\\\">Wolverine</a>, maybe.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>At around 15 per cent body fat, men will tend to start seeing&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/fast/one-move-full-body-workout\\\">muscular shape and definition</a>, while noticing changes in body composition and fat stores. Your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/4-moves-to-give-you-huge-arms\\\">arms</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workout/7-best-exercises-for-bigger-shoulders-fast\\\">shoulders</a>&nbsp;are more vascular too. You&rsquo;re now on-track for&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/10-minute-six-pack-workout\\\">a six-pack.</a></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>10% Body Fat</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br />\\r\\n<em>As a general rule of thumb, 10 per cent body fat is the safest place to be. You&rsquo;re lean enough to show muscle &mdash; including your six-pack &mdash; and you can see your veins from your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workout/7-best-exercises-for-bigger-shoulders-fast\\\">shoulders</a>&nbsp;to your hands, but you&rsquo;re not&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/watch-21-metabolic-moves-to-get-shredded\\\">so shredded</a>&nbsp;that you&rsquo;re becoming translucent. You need fat, after all, and having at least some body fat is absolutely vital for your body to operate normally.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Go below 10 per cent body fat and you enter the realm of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/food-nutrition/how-eating-like-a-professional-bodybuilder-can-make-you-fat\\\">bodybuilders</a>, poseurs and elite-level athletes&hellip;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>8% Body Fat (Or Under)</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&hellip;which brings you to single-digit body fat, our next and final stop.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Obtaining the coveted<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/a749616/can-i-get-in-shape-with-one-workout-a-week/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">&nbsp;single-digit body fat percentage</a>&nbsp;is usually reserved for the likes of race-car drivers gunning for optimum weight, fitness models getting ready for a shoot &mdash; who, most likely, have also dehydrated and carb-depleted for the last week &mdash; or Hollywood actors for a specific scene. What you must remember is that whilst single-digit is an aesthetically pleasing look for many, for the majority it&#39;s not practical to live by. In fact, even bodybuilders will often dip out of single-digit body fat only to shred hard in the weeks leading up to competition.Muscle loss, organ shrinking, nervous system damage, dehydration and fragile bone structure are all very real risks of low body fat. If this is a goal of yours, you have to approach with caution.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-12', './images/newsCms/Data/bfp2.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/549892_resized558846.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(425, 'How to Get Veins to Show on Your Arms', 'Welcome to the gun show', '<h2><em>1. Lower Body Fat Percentage</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If you&#39;re looking to get veins showing on your bicep, a good place to start is&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/this-guy-dropped-21-body-fat-building-his-best-ever-body\\\">lowering your body fat percentage.</a>&nbsp;Studies from the John Hopkins University show that low body fat can improve blood flow, allowing more oxygen to be delivered to the veins, blowing them up like a balloon. This will help uncover them from beneath your layer of skin.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Looking to burn body fat quick?</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>2. Reduce Sodium Intake</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>When you have a high sodium diet, your body retains more water. And while some gym-goers will use this tactic during festival season to expand their muscles, it certainly won&#39;t help with vascularity.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>The Australian recommended intake for sodium is only 460-920mg. To put that into perspective, a packet of plain potato chips contains between 170 and 185mg oer 28grams...yeah that&#39;s a lot. Because water is stored between the muscle and skin, not holding excess water will help bring veins to the surface.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>Increase Muscle Size</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Like the theme of the rest of this piece, reducing the space between your muscle and skin is crucial to having rivers flow down your forearms. Exercising will decrease body fat, helping you on your way but increasing muscle size will make that process even quicker. It&#39;s a win-win, you&#39;ll have more defined arms while getting enviable veins on your biceps. If you&#39;re after a temporary fix that will give you a good preview of what you&#39;re up for,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/bodyweight-exercises/resistance-bands-are-as-good-as-the-bench-press\\\">resistance training</a>&nbsp;can increase blood flow to your muscles exposing your veins.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>Drink More Water</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>While sodium increases water retention, drinking more water actually does the opposite. If you get through enough to H20 to help you visit the bathroom regularly, you&#39;ll flush out any excess water while retaining important minerals to help with muscle functionality. Restricting your water intake to reduce the amount under your skin works but is extremely dangerous. Think&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/food-nutrition/the-8-hours-diet-technique-that-helped-hugh-jackman-get-ripped\\\">Hugh Jackman</a>&nbsp;in Les Mis&eacute;rables.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/vein_arms.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/938600_resized414406.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(426, '3 Of The Craziest Tom Hardy Body Transformations', 'Hardy\'s got stacked (again) for Venom. MH charts his meteoric rise to Hollywood muscle', '<p><em>What do Charles Bronson, Mad Max, Bane, Reggie (and Ronnie) Kray and a hard-hitting, no-holds-barred UFC fighter all have in common?</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Do they all have a screw loose? Probably. Are they all played by Tom Hardy? Correct. Are each of them &mdash; in their own right &mdash; ruthless, totally cutthroat and in terrifying shape? Unquestionably.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Such has been the story of Tom Hardy&#39;s swashbuckling journey into Hollywood, with the 40-year-old having played some remarkable characters, including the notorious British criminal Charles Bronson &mdash; the &quot;most violent prisoner in Britain&quot;, according to some &mdash; Batman&#39;s hulking nemesis, Bane and Tommy Conlon, a bloodthirsty UFC fighter in 2011&#39;s&nbsp;Warrior.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Now, however, Tom Hardy&#39;s turning his attention to the world of Marvel, playing&nbsp;Spiderman&nbsp;villain Venom. Unsurprisingly, he&#39;s got into incredible shape for the role (again), using MMA and kickboxing training to strip fat.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Below, we detail Hardy&#39;s most impressive roles that required a total body overhaul, each contributing to his position in Hollywood today. Can&#39;t wait for Venom? This will help.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>Bronson (2008)</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Playing Britain&#39;s most violent criminal &mdash; who got a seven-year sentence for robbing a Post Office of &pound;26 &mdash; would take some work. Suitably, he helped pack on muscle using bodyweight (and prison-friendly) exercises including punishing&nbsp;<strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/the-genius-way-everybody-should-be-doing-press-ups\\\">press-up complexes</a></strong>. Impressive enough, but when you consider Hardy had to shed 12.5kg to play a homeless drug addict in&nbsp;Stuart: A Life Backwards&nbsp;only to bulk-up again for Bronson, his transformation becomes even more staggering.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&quot;I did non-specific exercises such as press-ups, push-ups, abs work and resistance training,&quot; says Hardy talking to Askmen about the role. &quot;To &ldquo;become&rdquo; Charlie Bronson I had to quickly put a lot of weight quickly on my forearms, chest and neck.&quot;</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>Warrior (2012)</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>To get into lean, Octagon-ready shape, Tom Hardy had to take a completely different approach to his fitness compared to that of&nbsp;Bronson. For his lead role opposite Joel Edgerton, Hardy dropped 15% off his body fat and packed on a whopping 20kg of lean, mean muscle.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Mastering boxing, Muay Thai, kickboxing and Jiu-Jitsu, he enveloped himself in the Warrior&#39;s code and taught himself to think, act and learn like a genuine UFC fighter.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&ldquo;Over time, technique wins over natural ability. People who work hard, with constant application, determination and tenacity &ndash; although they may not be as interesting, or have as much flair &ndash; will win,&quot; says Hardy. &quot;Overall, they will achieve a goal.&quot; And that&#39;s exactly what he did.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>&quot;Tom Hardy is such a professional that if he knows he absolutely has to do something, eventually he&rsquo;ll just get down to it,&quot; says his coach, trainer and friend Patrick &#39;Pnut&#39; Monroe, an ex-US Marine who&#39;s largely responsible for many of Tom Hardy&#39;s remarkable transformations.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Getting &quot;down to it&quot; meant a daily grind of the following: a 7am gym session, skipping, two hours of pad work, Muay Thai, a couple of hours of Jiu Jitsu, choreography and two more hours in the gym. A tall order, but the results speak for themselves.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><img alt=\\\"image\\\" src=\\\"https://hips.hearstapps.com/ame-prod-menshealth-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/main/assets/baneupload.jpg?resize=480:*\\\" /></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>The Dark Knight Rises (2012)</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>After losing 2.5 stone for&nbsp;Stuart: A Life Backwards, then gaining prison-yard muscle for&nbsp;Bronson&nbsp;and&nbsp;leaning out for ring-ready muscle for&nbsp;Warrior&nbsp;over the course of four years, Hardy was well-versed in what was required for Hollywood muscle by the time Christopher Nolan&#39;s The Dark Knight Rises came around in 2012.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>For the role, he had to put on 30lbs &mdash; that&#39;s 13kg, or two stone &mdash; in weight, bringing him to a number just shy of 200lbs, or 90kg. &quot;Compared to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/5-of-christian-bales-craziest-body-transformations\\\">Christian Bale</a></strong>&nbsp;I&rsquo;ve been by no means extreme in my body changes,&quot; 5ft 9in Hardy told The Daily Beast, answering concerns for his well-being following Bane&#39;s bulk-up.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Should you want to bulk-up like Bane himself</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/907292_resized89852.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(427, 'Why Calum von Moger\'s Chest Workout', 'Because sometimes the best workouts are the simplest ones', '<p>Australian bodybuilder and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/meet-the-guy-whos-playing-arnold-schwarzenegger-in-a-movie\\\">Arnold Schwarzenegger-to-be</a>&nbsp;Calum von Moger dropped a brand new video this week showing off a simple routine of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/bodyweight-exercises/crank-up-your-chest-without-lifting-weights-348714\\\">basic chest exercises</a>. Von Moger&#39;s pushing some serious weight here, as you might expect &mdash; he is a three-time Mr. Universe, after all &mdash; but the main focus here was on staying aware of his body&#39;s limitations.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Von Moger is still recovering from surgery to repair a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/5-best-bicep-exercises-you-arent-doing\\\">bicep</a>&nbsp;tear from last November, when a 400-lb. tandem curl stunt gone wrong put him in the hospital.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/watch-6-moves-you-should-do-before-every-workout\\\"><strong>(Related: 6 moves you should do before every workout)</strong></a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>He shed a light on just how much an&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/sports-injuries/10-ways-to-beat-muscle-soreness\\\">injury</a>&nbsp;can affect a bodybuilder&#39;s physique, warning his fans to learn from his mistakes and stay away from stupid stunts in the weight room. As Von Moger says, you should&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/a758949/back-to-basics-with-calum-von-mogers-4-move-chest-workout/true\\\">always make sure you warm up</a>&nbsp;before getting to your pump.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Calum von Moger&#39;s chest workout</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>His workout starts with an incline bench press &mdash; 10 reps at 100 kilos (about 220 lbs.), to be exact. If you can push that weight, you&#39;ve made it in von Moger&#39;s book. According to the video, this was the first time that he attempted a heavy incline press in the months following his injury.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>After incline, Von Moger moves over to the flat bench. Low cable flyes come next, followed by pec deck flyes. Machine tricep dips to finish the day.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/the-10-best-exercises-for-your-chest\\\"><strong>(Related: The 10 best exercises for your chest)</strong></a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you find yourself with an upper body injury like Von Moger, be smart with your recovery. You might not be Mr. Universe, but you can still hang on to your muscle using&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/5-ways-to-maintain-muscle-when-youre-injured\\\">these five tips</a>.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/fitness/a19640887/calum-von-moger-chest-workout/\\\"><em>A version of this article originally appeared on MensHealth.com</em></a></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image (1).jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/631788_resized569431.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(428, 'Jason Statham\'s action man workout', 'The fittest man in Hollywood swears by this \'Big Five-55\' routine from PT Dan John', '<p>Stuck for ideas? Statham&#39;s routine is the perfect antidote for a busy gym. If you can grab a squat-rack and an elevated box or bench, you won&#39;t need to move for the next 40 minutes. Read on for a big-screen back and enviable abs to match.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', 21, 82, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2020-12-30', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/378330_resized26229.jpg', 4, 'True'),
(429, 'Bulletproof Coffee: Everything You Need To Know', 'Plus, a nutritionist\'s opinion on the benefits of replacing your breakfast with bulletproof coffee', '<p><em>First thing in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/why-you-need-to-work-out-in-the-mornings\\\">the morning</a>&nbsp;can be a confusing time. You&rsquo;ve just woken up, you&rsquo;ve got to get to work and you need to find time to get some kind of healthy breakfast down your throat.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Sometimes there&rsquo;s just not enough time to do it all, so inevitably it&rsquo;s the breakfast that gets the heave-ho. But what if you could swap your healthy breakfast for a simple morning coffee that had a massive impact on your energy levels and cognitive function? You&rsquo;d go for that, surely? That&rsquo;s what bulletproof coffee promises to do &mdash; and a little more &mdash; but is it too good to be true? MH investigates.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>What is bulletproof coffee?</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>To make a bulletproof coffee you mix your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/healthy/addictions/9-ways-coffee-improves-your-health\\\">normal coffee</a>&nbsp;with grass-fed butter and an oil, such as coconut oil, which, according to its creators, creates a high-performance drink that can have a massive impact on your energy and cognitive function. The drink came about after an American health guru experienced drinking yak-butter tea at altitude in Tibet</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/cofeen.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/459746_resized761538.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(430, 'Six muscle-building nutrition rules', 'Follow this advice to get the most from your diet', '<p><em>1.Fuel before your workout</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Aim for 1g of carbohydrate to each 1&frasl;2g of protein an hour before your workout. This combination will give you extra energy to power your lift.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>2.Eat 2g protein for every kilo of body weight</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>This is essential to build muscle and keep blood-sugar levels constant. So stock up on lean meats like turkey and chicken, as well as tuna and a few choices cut of beef.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>3.Bulk up with yoghurt</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Pour it over fresh fruit for breakfast, or have a pot for dessert. Its high calcium has been proven to increase muscle growth.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>4.Time your refuel</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Consume essential amino acids (found in protein and carbohydrates) after resistance training, and every hour for 4 hours thereafter. This will maximize new muscle growth.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>5.Complement with veg</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>A high-protein diet is very acidic and could affect bone density. Counter this by eating vegetable proteins such as beans, lentils, raw nuts and seeds.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>6.Supplement your diet with nitric acid</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Found in beans, fish and soy, it increases the size of the blood vessels in your muscles, so you can work harder.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image (2).jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/87244_resized690319.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(431, 'Q. If I shave my chest will the hair grow back thicker?', 'MH’s Online Grooming Editor dispels a few myths about hair removal', '<h2><em>All questions answered</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Q. If I shave my chest will the hair grow back thicker?</strong></em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>A.</strong>&nbsp;In a word, no. It&rsquo;s a myth that shaving makes hair grow back thicker, and it does not increase overall hair growth so that you get hairier &ndash; imagine how furry your face would be if it did.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>So where does this misconception come from? Well, the truth is that when you shave your chest the hair does tend to&nbsp;look&nbsp;thicker when it grows back. This is because shaving slices off the tips of the hair, leaving the ends blunt and more noticeable once re-growth occurs. You get an initial stubbly look, too, until the hairs are a few millimetres long.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>If this is a look you&rsquo;re not keen on, then the simple solution is to switch to waxing, sugaring or a depilatory cream. All of these methods remove the hair at the root and ensure that when the hairs grow back they do so with fine, soft tips which (a) don&rsquo;t itch and (b) don&rsquo;t look quite so thick. There&rsquo;s another big benefit too: shaving will only keep the hair at bay for a few days but removing it at the root will give you a smooth chest for weeks.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>What to use</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Nad&#39;s For Men Hands Free Hair Removal Cream</strong>, &pound;7.16 for 200ml from&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/Nads-Men-Hair-Removal-Cream/dp/B003JFJF5E?tag=menshealth.co.uk-21&amp;ascsubtag=[artid|1930.a.747237[src|[ch|\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><strong>amazon.co.uk</strong></a>. Easy-to-use cream that&rsquo;s especially formulated for male body hair and washes off (along with the unwanted hairs) in the shower.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>M4Men Hair Removal System Starter Kit</strong>, &pound;14.65 from&nbsp;<strong><a href=\\\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/M4MEN-Hair-Removal-System-12oz/dp/B000VS96L0?tag=menshealth.co.uk-21&amp;ascsubtag=[artid|1930.a.747237[src|[ch|\\\">a</a><a href=\\\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/M4MEN-Hair-Removal-System-12oz/dp/B000VS96L0?tag=menshealth.co.uk-21&amp;ascsubtag=[artid|1930.a.747237[src|[ch|\\\">mazon</a>.co.uk</strong>&nbsp;Ideal for sensitive skin this treatment gives long-lasting results without blunt-ended, itchy re-growth and isn&rsquo;t quite as eye-watering as some waxes.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Elemis Tea Tree SOS Spray,</strong>&nbsp;&pound;17.60 for 60ml from&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.mankind.co.uk/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><strong>mankind.co.uk</strong></a>. With its naturally antiseptic properties, this spray is the perfect after treatment for freshly de-fuzzed skin, helping prevent rashes, sensitivity and irritation.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><em>Did you know?</em></h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>A recent survey by&nbsp;The Daily Telegraph&nbsp;revealed that nearly 1 in 10 men steal their partner&rsquo;s hair removal cream or wax to use on themselves.</em></p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2020-12-27', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image (3).jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/258429_resized505573.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(432, 'Jumping Jacks ', '    CHEST', 'Start with your feet together and your arms by your sides, then jump up with your feet apart and your hands overhead.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nReturn to the start position then do the next rep. This exercise provides a full-body workout and works all your large muscle groups\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(433, 'Knee Push-ups', '        CHEST', 'Start in the regular push-up position, then let your knees touch the floor and raise your feet up off the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nNext push your body up and down\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(434, 'Push-ups', '        CHEST', 'Lay prone on the ground with arms supporting your body.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nKeep your body straight while raising and lowering your body with your arms.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThis exercise works the chest, shoulders, triceps, back and legs.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(435, 'Wide Arm Push-ups ', '         CHEST', 'Start in the regular push-up position but with your hands spread wider than your shoulders.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen push your body up and down. Remember to keep your body straight\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(436, 'Hindu Push-ups ', '        CHEST', 'Start with your hands and feet touching the floor, body bent and butt up in an upside down &#39;V&#39; shape.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen bend your elbows to bring your body towards the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nWhen your body is close to the floor, raise your upper body up as far as possible. Then return to the original position and repeat\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(437, 'Staggered Push-ups ', '         CHEST', 'Start in the regular push-up position, but with one hand in front of the other.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen do a push-up and switch the other hand in front.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRemember to keep your body straight\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(438, 'Push -up & Rotation', '         CHEST', 'Start in the push-up position. Then go down for a push-up and as you come up, rotate your upper body and extend your right arm upwards.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRepeat the exercise with the other arm. It&#39;s a great exercise for the chest, shoulders, arms and core\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(439, 'Knee Push- ups', '         CHEST', 'Start in the regular push-up position, then let your knees touch the floor and raise your feet up off the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nNext push your body up and down\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-10', '2029-12-10', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(440, 'Decline Push-ups', '         CHEST', 'Start on all fours with your knees under your butt and your hands under your shoulders.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen elevate your feet on a chair or bench, and push your body up and down mainly using your arm strength.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRemember to keep your body straight.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(441, 'Shoulder Stretch', '         CHEST', 'Place one arm across your body, parallel to the ground, then use the other arm to pull the parallel arm toward your chest.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nHold for a while, switch arms and repeat the exercise. Keep the inside arm straight during the exercise\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(442, 'Cobra Stretch', '        CHEST', 'Lie down on your stomach and bend your elbows with your hands beneath your shoulders.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen push your chest up off the ground as far as possible. Hold this position for seconds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(443, 'Jumping Jacks', 'ABS', 'Start with your feet together and your arms by your sides, then jump up with your feet apart and your hands overhead.&nbsp; \\r\\n\\r\\n Return to the start position then do the next rep. This exercise provides a full-body workout and works all your large muscle groups. \\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2020-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(444, 'Heel Touch', '    ABS', 'Lie on the ground with your legs bent and your arms by your sides.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nSlightly lift your upper body off the floor and make your hands alternately reach your heels\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True');
INSERT INTO `f_newscms_data_2019` (`id`, `posttitle`, `shortdescription`, `fulldescription`, `category_id`, `subcategory_id`, `post_active`, `post_startdate`, `post_enddate`, `post_image`, `post_imageresized`, `postdisplay_order`, `post_front`) VALUES
(445, 'Crossover Crunch', '    ABS', 'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your hands behind your ears.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise and twist your torso so your right elbow moves to meet your left knee. Repeat with the other side.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-27', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(446, 'Mountain Climber', '    ABS', 'Start in the push-up position. Bend your right knee towards your chest and keep your left leg straight, then quickly switch from one leg to the other.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThis exercise strengthens multiple muscle groups\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(447, 'Side Bridges Right & Lift ', '    ABS', 'Lie on your right side. Put your right elbow directly under your shoulders and put your left hand on your waist. Place your left leg on your right leg.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise your hips upward, hold for 2-4 seconds, then go back to the start position.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(448, 'Butt Bridge ', '    ABS', 'Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Put your arms flat at your sides.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your butt up and down.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(449, 'Bicycle Crunches', '    ABS', 'Lie on the floor with your hands behind your ears. Raise your knees and close your right elbow toward your left knee, then close your left elbow toward your right knee. Repeat the exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(450, 'V-UP', '    ABS', 'Lie on your back with your arms and legs extended and your legs squeezed together.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise your upper body and legs, use your arms to touch your toes, then go back to the start position and repeat the exercise\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(451, 'V-UP', '    ABS', 'Lie on your back with your arms and legs extended and your legs squeezed together.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise your upper body and legs, use your arms to touch your toes, then go back to the start position and repeat the exercise\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(452, 'Abdomminal Crunches', '    ABS', 'Lie on your back with your knees bent and your arms stretched forward.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your upper body off the floor. Hold for a few seconds and slowly return.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nIt primarily works the rectus abdominis muscle and the obliques\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(453, 'Plank', '    ABS', 'Lie on the floor with your toes and forearms on the ground. Keep your body straight and hold this position as long as you can.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThis exercise strengthens the abdomen, back and shoulders.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(454, 'Leg Raises', '    ABS', 'Lie down on your back, and put your hands beneath your hips for support.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your legs up until they form a right angle with the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nSlowly bring your legs back down and repeat the exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(455, 'Arm Circles Clockwise', '    ABS', 'Stand on the floor with your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder height.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nMove your arms clockwise in circles fast.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nTry to do it as fast as you can.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nIt&#39;s a great exercise for the deltoid muscle\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(456, 'Floor Tricep Dips ', '    ABS', 'Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Put your hands beneath your shoulders with your fingers pointing toward your hips.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nLift your hips off the floor. Then bend and extend your elbows to lower and lift your hips.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRepeat the exercise to strengthen your upper arms.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(457, 'Miltary Push-Ups', '    ARM', 'Start in a push-up position with your hands directly under your shoulders and feet no more than 12 inches apart.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nBend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Stay in this position for one second and then push your body back to the starting position and repeat the exercise. Please remember that your elbows should be close to your body during this exercise\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '0219-01-28', '2029-12-30', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(458, 'Alternating Hooks', '     ARM', 'Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, and place your dominant foot slightly forward. Slightly bend your knees, clench your fists and bend your elbows at 90 degrees.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise your right arm to shoulder height and keep your forearm parallel to the ground. Rotate your shoulders and hips and punch towards the left. Switch sides and repeat.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2019-12-30', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(459, 'Push-up & Rotation', '          ARM', 'Start in the push-up position. Then go down for a push-up and as you come up, rotate your upper body and extend your right arm upwards.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRepeat the exercise with the other arm. It&#39;s a great exercise for the chest, shoulders, arms and core.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(460, 'Leg Barbell Curl Left & Right', '         ARM', 'Stand against a wall. Lift your right leg up, lean forward and grab underneath your right ankle with your left hand.&nbsp; \\r\\n\\r\\n Bring the ankle up towards the shoulder as much as you can, then lower it and repeat the exercise. \\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(461, 'Skipping Without Rope ', '         ARM', 'Place your arms at your sides and pretend to hold a skipping rope handle in each hand.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nJump and alternately land on the balls of your feet, rotating your wrists at the same time as if you were spinning a rope.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(462, 'Push-ups', '         ARM', 'Lay prone on the ground with arms supporting your body.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nKeep your body straight while raising and lowering your body with your arms.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThis exercise works the chest, shoulders, triceps, back and legs.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(463, 'Burpees', '         ARM', 'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, then put your hands on the ground and kick your feet backward. Do a quick push-up and then jump up\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(464, 'Arm Scissors', '         ARM', 'Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nStretch your arms in front of you at shoulder height with one arm overlap the other in the shape of the letter &ldquo;X&rdquo;, and then spread them apart\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(465, 'Triceps Stretch Left & Right ', '         ARM', 'Put your left hand on your back, use your right hand to grab your left elbow and gently pull it. Hold this position for a few seconds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-01-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(466, 'Standing Biceps Stretch Left & Right', '          ARM', 'Stand with your left arm close to a wall. Extend your left arm and put your left hand on the wall, then gently turn your body to the right &amp; left\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-30', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(467, 'Jumping Jacks', 'SHOULDER & BACK', 'Start with your feet together and your arms by your sides, then jump up with your feet apart and your hands overhead.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nReturn to the start position then do the next rep. This exercise provides a full-body workout and works all your large muscle groups.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(468, 'Triceps Kickbacks', '     SHOULDER & BACK', 'Lean forward, bend your knees and your elbows.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nExtend your arms behind you and squeeze your triceps. Please make your arms parallel to the ground when extending them.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nGo back to the start position, and repeat this exercis\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(469, 'Incline Push-up', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Start in the regular push-up position but with your hands elevated on a chair or bench.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen push your body up down using your arm strength.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRemember to keep your body straight\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(470, 'Rhomboid Pulls', '     SHOULDER & BACK', 'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRaise your arms parallel to the ground, and bend your elbows. Pull your elbows back and squeeze your shoulder blades.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nRepeat this exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(471, 'Floor Tricep Dips', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Put your hands beneath your shoulders with your fingers pointing toward your hips.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nLift your hips off the floor. Then bend and extend your elbows to lower and lift your hips.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(472, 'Cat Cow Pose', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Start on all fours with your knees under your butt and your hands directly under your shoulders.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen take a breath and make your belly fall down, shoulders roll back and head come up towards the ceiling\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(474, 'Hip Hinge', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nSit your hips back and bend your upper body while keeping your upper body straight, then slowly go back to the start position and repeat the exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-29', '2029-12-29', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(475, 'Side-Lying Floor Stretch Right & lift ', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Lie on your right side with your right knee slightly bent in front of you and your left leg stretched behind the right leg.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nStraighten your left arm over your head and gently pull on your left wrist to stretch the left side of your body.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nHold this position for a few seconds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-29', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(476, 'Hover Push Up ', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Start in a push-up position. Lower yourself; shift your body to the left and then to the right.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nPush your body up and repeat the exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(477, 'Swimmer & Superman', '     SHOULDER & BACK', 'Lie on your stomach with your arms extended straight overhead. Alternately lift your opposite arm and leg.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(478, 'Child\'s Pose', '    SHOULDER & BACK', 'Start with your knees and hands on the floor. Put your hands a little forward, widen your knees and put your toes together.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nTake a breath, then exhale and sit back. Try to make your butt touch your heels. Relax your elbows, make your forehead touch the floor and try to lower your chest close to the floor. Hold this position.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nKeep your arms stretched forward as you sit back. Make sure there is enough space between your shoulders and ears during the exercise.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(479, 'Jumping Jacks', 'LEG', 'Start with your feet together and your arms by your sides, then jump up with your feet apart and your hands overhead.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nReturn to the start position then do the next rep. This exercise provides a full-body workout and works all your large muscle groups.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 91, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(480, 'Squats', '    LEG', 'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and your arms stretched forward, then lower your body until your thighs are parallel with the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nYour knees should be extended in the same direction as your toes. Return to the start position and do the next rep.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThis works the thighs, hips buttocks, quads, hamstrings and lower body\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(481, 'Fire Hydrant Left & Right', '    LEG', 'Start on all fours with your knees under your butt and your hands under your shoulders.&nbsp; \\r\\n\\r\\n Then lift your left leg to the side at a 90 degree angle. \\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(482, 'Lunges', '     LEG', 'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and your hands on your hips.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nTake a step forward with your right leg and lower your body until your right thigh is parallel with the floor.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen return and switch to the other leg. This exercise strengthens the quadriceps, gluteus maximus and hamstrings.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(483, 'Side Leg Circles Left & Right', '    LEG', 'Lie on your right side with your head resting on your right hand.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your left leg and rotate your foot in circles\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your right leg and rotate your foot in circles.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-29', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(484, 'Sumo Squat', '    LEG', 'Stand with your feet 6-12 inches apart. Stretch your arms in front of you.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nLower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Return to the starting position and repeat the exercise\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(485, 'Reverse Flutter Kicks', '    LEG', 'Lie face down on a bench, place your butt on the edge of the bench and hold on to the sides.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThen lift your legs until they are level with your upper body.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nLift one leg higher than the other, then switch to the other leg and repeat\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(486, 'Wall Set', '    LEG', 'Start with your back against the wall, then slide down until your knees are at a 90 degree angle.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nKeep your back against the wall with your hands and arms away from your legs. Hold the position.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(487, 'Left & Right Quad Stretch With Wall', '    LEG', 'Stand with your right hand on the wall. Bend your left leg and grasp your ankle or toes to bring your left calf close to your left thigh. Hold this position.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-29', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(488, 'Knee To Chest Stretch Left & Right', '     LEG', 'Lie on the floor with your legs extended. Lift your left knee up and grab it with both hands.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nPull your left knee towards your chest as much as you can while keeping your right leg straight on the ground.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nHold this position for a few seconds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(489, 'Calf Raise With Splayed Foot ', '    LEG', 'Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Put your hands on the wall to maintain balance.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nTwist your ankles to make your toes point outwards, then lift your heels up and down.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(490, 'Single Leg Calf Hop Left & Right', '    LEG', 'Stand straight with your right leg lifted. Then hop up and down on your left foot. \\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-28', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(491, 'Calf Stretch Left', '    LEG', 'Stand one big step away in front of a wall. Step forward with your right foot and push the wall with your hands.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nPlease make sure your left leg is fully extended and you can feel your left calf stretching. Hold this position for a few seconds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 23, 95, 'True', '2019-01-28', '2029-12-31', '', '', 0, 'True'),
