(506, 'الزمالك يسقط أمام جورماهيا برباعية في الكونفدرالية', '     ', '<p><em>استهل نادي الزمالك، مشواره في دور المجموعات لبطولة الكونفدرالية الأفريقية بالخسارة من مضيفه جورماهيا الكيني بثلاثة أهداف مقابل هدفين، في مباراة كان عنوانها الأخطاء الدفاعية للأبيض.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وفرط الزمالك في تقدمه بهدف ليتقدم عليه جورماهيا بهدفين ثم ينهي الأبيض الشوط الأول متقدما، قبل أن يسجل أصحاب الأرض الهدفين الثالث والرابع في الشوط الثاني.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>بدأت المباراة بشكل سريع، وضغط جورماهيا في محاولة لفرض أسلوبه على الزمالك.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وفي الدقيقة الثالثة تعرض لاعب جورماهيا لإصابة قوية إثر تدخل من طلاق حامد لاعب وسط الزمالك، ليتوقف اللعب لعلاج اللاعب.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ورغم البداية التي غلب عليها أفضلية نسبية للفريق الكيني، إلا أن الزمالك باغت أصحاب الأرض بهدف من تسديدة إبراهيم حسن سكنت الشباك في الدقيقة السادسة لتمنح التقدم للأبيض.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>بعد الهدف بات الزمالك أكثر قربا لتسجيل المزيد، وفي الدقيقة 18 أرسل أوباما كرة عرضية لكنها ذهبت باتجاه المرمى لتصطدم بالعارضة وتمر بعيدا.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>واستفاد الزمالك من فقدان لاعبي جورماهيا الكرة بشكل سريع، ومن تمريرة كهربا إلى فرجاني ساسي سدد التونسي باتجاه المرمى ولكن تسديدته لم تكن بالقوة الكافية.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ونجح جورماهيا في تعديل النتيجة، من خطأ دفاعي متكرر للزمالك، وسوء تغطية في كرة عرضية من جهة اليسار عن طريق جاك تيوسينجي هداف الفريق في الدقيقة 26.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ومن خطأ لجنش اقترب جورماهيا من مرمى الزمالك من جديد، قبل أن يصحح الحارس والقائد أوضاعه ويمسك بالكرة.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ويبعد جنش فرصة أخرى خطيرة بعد هجمة مرتدة سريعة للفريق الكيني في الدقيقة 33.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وعاد جورماهيا من جديد في هجمة بكثافة عددية مقابل غياب دفاعي واضح، لتضيع الفرصة التهديفية المحققة بعدما أنقذها جنش.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ومن فرصة أخرى في الدقيقة 38، نجح تيوسينجي، في تسجيل الهدف الثاني لجورماهيا ليتقدم على الزمالك، لتظل أزمة الكرات العرضية وسوء التعامل معها.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وقبل نهاية الشوط الأول نجح الزمالك في تعديل النتيجة والعودة لنقطة الصفر، من خلال إبراهيم حسن صاحب الهدف الأول، حيث تسلم تمريرة كهربا لينفرد بالمرمى، ويجسل الثاني.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>بدأ الزمالك الشوط الثاني بشكل أفضل وأكثر تماسكا، لكن جورماهيا استغل الدفاعي السيء للفريق الأبيض في الدقيقة السادسة، عن طريق كيبكروي في الدقيقة السادسة.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وكاد الزمالك يتعادل عن طريق عبدالله جمعة، لكن الكرة ابعدها الدفاع من أمام خط المرمى.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>استمر سيناريو الشوط الثاني بضغط زملكاوي ومحاولات خطيرة من مرتدات جورماهيا، وأجرى كريستيان جروس مدرب الزمالك تبديلين هجوميين على مدار الشوط الثاني، حيث دفع بعمر السعيد على حساب كهربا الذي أضاع فرصة خطيرة على خط المرمى، وشارك حميد أحداد على حساب صاحب هدفي الزمالك إبراهيم حسن.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>ولم تغير التبديلات نتيجة المباراة، في حين ظهر أحداد في واحدة من أبرز المحاولات باختراق ومحاولة وسقوط إثر كرة مشتركة أشار الحكم فيها باستمرار اللعب.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>وفي اللحظات الأخيرة نجح البديل أوليتش في تسجيل الهدف الرابع من مراوغة للحارس جنش بعد خطأ دفاعي ساذج.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>الخسارة أبقت الزمالك بلا نقاط في بداية مرحلة المجموعات انتظارا لمباراة نصر حسين داي الجزائري مع بترو أتلتيكو الأنجولي</em></p>\\r\\n', 3, 15, 'True', '2019-02-03', '2019-03-03', './images/newsCms/Data/201902030343484348.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/656919_resized642650.jpg', 1, 'True'),
(507, 'Watch: This guy lost 42 pounds in 12 weeks', 'Hunter Hobbs reveals how he carved that six-pack', '<p>Think&nbsp;New Year&#39;s resolutions&nbsp;never really amount to much? Hunter Hobbs will certainly have you thinking otherwise.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The 24-year-old recently posted a video on Facebook showing off his&nbsp;incredible body transformation. The Norman, Oklahoma, native took a shirtless photo of himself every day for three months straight, then put all the photos together in a 55-second time lapse video.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The video shows Hobbs transforming from from 202 pounds to 160 pounds &mdash; a total loss of 42 pounds &mdash; over the course of 12 weeks. While the 55-second video makes the transformation go by in a mesmerising blur, it certainly didn&#39;t come quickly or easily, Hobbs said.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hobbs explained that he had always been a pretty fit person, but after he graduated college two years ago and started a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/healthy/symptoms-treatment/how-can-i-make-a-desk-job-healthy\\\">full-time desk job</a>&nbsp;with an oil and gas company, his physical health took a back seat.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;I was at a point when I needed to get back in shape,&quot; Hobbs said. &quot;I wondered, if I really committed for three months and went all out, what I could accomplish. I also have a passion for making videos, so I thought I could come up with something really cool.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Pictured above at 202 pounds, Hobbs was the heaviest he had ever been. Determined to make a change, starting January 1st, Hobbs took a shirtless photo a day and got to work.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Hobbs&#39; workout plan</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;I started off&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/why-lifting-heavy-and-eating-more-is-the-best-way-to-lose-fat\\\">lifting heavy in the gym</a>, doing sets of six to eight reps, going five to six times a week,&quot; he said. &quot;After four or five weeks of that, I switched to higher reps, 10-12, and lower weights,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/blogs/be-your-own-personal-trainer/be-your-own-personal-trainer-tempo-blog\\\">but upped the intensity</a>.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hobbs added in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/lose-weight/is-cardio-necessary-for-single-digit-body-fat\\\">cardio</a>&nbsp;whenever he could, usually for 20-30 minutes after he was done lifting.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;I did a lot of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/cardio-exercise/get-stacked-on-the-treadmill\\\">incline on the treadmill,</a>&nbsp;maxing out the incline and walking at about four miles per hour,&quot; he said. &quot;If I didn&#39;t do the treadmill, I&#39;d do the Stairmaster.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Pictured above is Hobbs on February 17, just as he was starting to switch away&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/are-heavy-weights-really-better-for-building-muscle\\\">from heavier lifting</a>&nbsp;to lighter, more intense sessions with additional cardio. Hobbs said that for the last few weeks of his 12-week programme, he added in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/running/how-to-burn-more-fat-with-interval-training\\\">sprint intervals</a>&nbsp;on the treadmill, doing sets of 45 seconds sprinting, 45 seconds recovering.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Hobbs&#39; eating plan</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hobbs already had a background in working out, having been pretty consistent with it in college. The real challenge was changing his diet. Through researching online and consulting a couple of friends, Hobbs got an idea of how many calories he should be eating and what types of foods would work best for him.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;My diet was pretty basic &mdash; oatmeal, chicken, eggs, spinach salads &mdash; and I stayed really consistent with it,&quot; he said. &quot;I packed my lunch every single day.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hobbs thinks his nutrition made the biggest difference in his results.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;The toughest part of this whole thing was people around me eating stuff I couldn&#39;t,&quot; he said. &quot;Especially my roommate. One day, I got back from the gym and said, &#39;Man, I&#39;m really craving a pizza,&#39; and my roommate said, &#39;That&#39;s a great idea,&#39; and ordered a large pizza and ate it in front of me.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It was apparently worth it &mdash; below is Hobbs at the end of his 12-week transformation, 42 pounds lighter.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Moving forward</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Now what&#39;s his plan? Relax a little bit, but not too much.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;I&#39;ve gotten into a great routine both at the gym and with making my own meals, so I&#39;m definitely going to stick to that,&quot; Hobbs said. &quot;But I&#39;m not going to feel bad if I go out and have a few drinks with my friends every once in a while or go out for a nice dinner.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hey, everyone deserves a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/food-nutrition/how-to-burn-fat-on-cheat-day\\\">cheat meal</a>&nbsp;now and then.</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-02-06', '2020-10-20', '', '', 0, 'True'),
(508, '5 Things I Learnt During My Transformation', 'At the age of 43, this dad of two proves that it\'s never too late to get fit and healthy. The message is simple: find something you love doing and you\'ll never stop', '<p>Three months ago, MH sent an email out across the company titled &ldquo;Are you a man? And do you want to change your life?&rdquo;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/a759544/chris-hemsworth-shares-his-best-fitness-advice-for-busy-dads/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Busy and tired dad of two</a>&nbsp;Lewis Hammond saw this as the perfect opportunity to overhaul his health, not just for himself, but for his family. Over the course of 12 weeks, Lewis has seen first-hand the power of working out,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/nutrition/a759671/i-tried-the-carnivore-diet-heres-what-happened/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">eating well</a>&nbsp;and making his wellbeing a priority.&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\nFrom losing over 7kg of fat and 9 per cent&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workouts/g759733/fight-away-winter-fat-with-this-3-part-workout/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">body fat</a>, to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a754623/drop-your-high-blood-pressure-in-2-months-with-blueberries/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">lowering his blood pressure</a>, improving his sleep and of course,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/a759235/best-chest-exercises-for-building-muscle/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">adding serious muscle mass to his frame</a>, Lewis has become a new man. He told us exactly what he learnt about himself over the course of 12 weeks to show you that by setting goals and with dedication, a better you is just 12 weeks away.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><em><strong>Read the full story plus his workout plan in the latest issue of Men&#39;s Health</strong></em></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&quot;Before I start, I just want to explain that I never did this for the aesthetic. What I wanted out of this was to feel mentally fresh,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/search/?q=back+injury\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">cure my back injury,</a>&nbsp;which I had suffered with in relative silence for years, get back on the rugby pitch, have more energy to play with my kids and generally be a happier person once again. I wanted to prove that it&#39;s never too late to get back on the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/fitness/a758385/the-two-moves-that-will-keep-you-fit-for-life/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">fitness train, to reclaim your fitness</a>. I&#39;ve found something I enjoy and I won&#39;t stop. So in that respect, I achieved everything I wanted to.&quot;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>No Surprise, but I Used to Eat Too Much</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<ol>\\r\\n	</ol>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<ol>\\r\\n	</ol>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/search/?q=portion\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">By too much I mean portion sizes</a>. I was raised to finish my plate, and with little self-restraint over how much I could eat, I would just eat what I cooked. And I always cooked too much.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I also thought what I was eating was healthy. I used extra virgin olive oil, had decent amounts of salad on the side of my plate and ate a varied diet.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>But then I had my blood tests and found out things weren&rsquo;t so rosy in my garden. A lifetime of saying yes to everything had taken its toll.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>So Callum, my trainer, got me to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/nutrition/a759564/study-suggests-eating-cheeseburgers-might-be-good-for-your-health/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">dial down the red meat</a>, dial up the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/search/?q=fish\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">white fish</a>, weigh how much rice I cooked (65g and no more!), change my breakfast routine and introduce 1-Cal olive oil spray into my life. And I haven&rsquo;t looked back.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>I Could Never Give up Chocolate, but Then I Didn&rsquo;t Really Need To</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I always thought that to achieve results from a transformation such as this, I would have to give up everything I held dear, like my very worst habits.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>I Didn&rsquo;t Know the First Thing about Achieving Sustainable Good Health</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I thought that the occasional run-out on the rugby pitch and the odd banana would allow me to pretty much do what I wanted in terms of the rest of my diet. I thought I looked OK (for a 43 year old), if a little shapeless these days. But then my scans told me that my visceral (hidden) fat was at uncomfortable levels. And there&rsquo;s nothing like a professional telling you something has to change for it to actually.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>So I needed to heed the advice of the experts at the Third Space, and cut out the bad things that had become staples in my life &ndash;&nbsp;those all too frequent lunchtime pints, dairy (<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/nutrition/a759494/6-dairy-free-foods-that-are-high-in-calcium/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">I love milk!</a>), various fast foods. I had to re-find that inner voice I had from my youth, which would whisper in my ear that I didn&#39;t need that bag of crisps, that I would feel better if I put on my gear and went for a late night power walk in the rain. I can do this in 12 weeks. I will train on my holidays, because others wouldn&#39;t. That voice was in there all along, I just listen to it more now.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>I Now Understand the Point of a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/a757114/7-personal-trainer-secrets-to-pump-up-your-arms/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Personal Trainer</a></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Before, I was sceptical of their benefits, but then Callum taught me about many things:</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>- The power of diet (&ldquo;80 per cent of my transformation would be about what I ate&rdquo;)</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>- What the backs of packets mean</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>- What my&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a759284/7-best-exercises-to-lower-your-cholesterol/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">optimum fat burn heart rate is</a>&nbsp;(and how to achieve it)</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>- How to vary my workout so that I was never stressing the same muscles all of the time</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/building-muscle/a759037/how-to-get-stronger-by-cutting-your-lifts-in-half/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">How to push myself to lift weights until failure</a>&nbsp;(as those last few reps that you don&rsquo;t think you can do on your own are the most important for muscle gain)</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-02-06', '2019-05-31', './images/newsCms/Data/safe_image (1).jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/42560_resized879118.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(509, '5 Benefits of Training in the Cold', 'Put your excuses on ice. Brave the plummeting mercury and you can fire up any fitness plan', '<h3><strong>Warning Signs</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<ol>\\r\\n	</ol>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The shock you feel when you swap your duvet for the frosty pavement is physiologically unavoidable. But the shiver up your spine signals&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/workouts/g759168/20-minutes-to-fire-up-your-metabolism-and-burn-fat/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">that your metabolism is revving up</a>. Your body is hard-wired to prefer storing fat over burning it, so it sends you a warning that you&rsquo;re at risk of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/nutrition/a759590/think-you-can-handle-the-rocks-calories/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">expending your stockpiled calories</a>. That&rsquo;s the point &ndash; so push on.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Extra Time</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your body now starts to convert &ldquo;lazy&rdquo; white fat cells &ndash; used for energy storage &ndash; into calorie-melting beige cells. Researchers at the CU Sports Medicine and Performance Center in Colorado found that regular exposure to the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/nutrition/a758703/eat-breakfast-after-the-gym-for-a-spiked-metabolism/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">cold causes your metabolism&nbsp;</a>to switch from predominantly burning carbohydrates to torching fat: equivalent to doing seven hours&rsquo; extra cardio per week.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Maximum Air</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The cold causes your body to continue making subtle adaptations: your blood vessels narrow, and your heart and lungs work harder. This helps to improve your muscles&rsquo; aerobic function, meaning they receive more oxygen during exercise. An animal study by Northern Arizona University suggests it can increase your VO2 max by 34% and your long-distance running speed by 29%</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Freeze Out Flu</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you think all of this hard work will play havoc on your immune system (which is&nbsp;<br />\\r\\nbad news in the season of the office lurgy), have no fear. In reality, the chill primes your defences. According to the Mayo Foundation for Medical Education and Research in&nbsp;<br />\\r\\nthe US,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a759455/best-ways-to-get-rid-of-colds/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">regular cold-weather training could cut your risk of man flu by 20-30%</a>. Fight fire with ice, essentially.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Cold Comforts</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Maintain your outdoor training all winter and you&rsquo;ll promote the release of mood-enhancing hormones beta-endorphin and noradrenaline &ndash; which, combined with the endorphins released by exercise, will help you to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/mental-strength/a759636/the-5-women-who-helped-me-fight-depression/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">ward off seasonal depression</a>. These biological benefits will also&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a758381/6-obvious-signs-that-show-youre-stressed/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">make everyday stresses&nbsp;</a>such as snow day traffic and not being able to find your thermal underwear more manageable</p>\\r\\n', 19, 83, 'True', '2019-02-06', '2019-04-06', './images/newsCms/Data/sports-clothing-royalty-free-image-850895008-1546610117.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/15096_resized635036.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(510, 'El Clasico: Lionel Messi guessing game dominates Barcelona v Real Madrid', '    ', 'The first of three Clasicos in the space of less than a month takes place on Wednesday night as&nbsp;Barcelona&nbsp;host Real Madrid in the Copa del Rey semi-final first leg.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nBoth clubs would readily admit that the cup comes third on their list of priorities for the season, and respective managers Ernesto Valverde and Santiago Solari have heavily rotated their starting line-ups during the earlier rounds.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nHowever, the high profile of a Clasico contest &ndash; and the bragging rights which will inevitably follow &ndash; could tempt the coaches to field their strongest possible line-ups at the Camp Nou. But for Barca, the question of whether that will include their key player is the main talking point, and the first of our three big questions ahead of the game:\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nMESSI TO BE RISKED?\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nBarcelona are sweating on the fitness of captain Lionel Messi after the Argentine took a bang to his thigh during the 2-2 draw with Valencia at the weekend, and Valverde &ndash; and Messi himself &ndash; are being forced to decide whether they are prepared to take any risks or let Messi fully recover for the tough run of games that lie ahead.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThe next few weeks will see Barca face tough trips to Athletic Bilbao, Sevilla, Madrid and Real Betis in La Liga, as well as resuming their Champions League campaign with a round-of-16 tie against Lyon. Having Messi available for those games is a much bigger priority than taking a gamble to proceed in the Copa &ndash; irrespective of the identity of their semi-final opponents &ndash; and it would be a dangerous game if Barca rush back their star man for this first leg.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThe need for Messi to play is pronounced by the fact that Ousmane Dembele is still missing, despite returning to training following an ankle injury. Dembele resumed training on Monday, but he has also been suffering with illness and has not been named in the squad.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nHowever, Barca&rsquo;s concerns over heading into a Clasico without Messi will be assuaged by the fact that they did exactly that during the Argentine&rsquo;s injury absence in October, and still managed to win 5-1.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nSELECTION DILEMMAS IN MIDFIELD BATTLEGROUND\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nIf Messi is able to play, that could mean a relegation to the bench for Philippe Coutinho, who is continuing to struggle for form.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nCoutinho&rsquo;s chances of starting are enhanced by the ongoing absence of Dembele, but manager Valverde is weighing up the option of seeking to control the contest by strengthening his midfield.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nBarca have generally lined up in a 4-3-3 formation this season, but last year they played plenty of games in a 4-4-2 shape with Messi and Suarez up front, and there is a convincing argument that Arturo Vidal should be selected for his physical capabilities to complement the more technical skills of Arthur, Ivan Rakitic and Sergio Busquets, while youngster Carles Alenya also looks worthy of more playing time.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nMadrid boss Solari, likewise, has plenty of possibilities for his three midfield places. Dani Ceballos, Marcos Llorente and out-of-favour Isco are competing to substitute regular starters Casemiro, Toni Kroos and Luka Modric &ndash; especially with Saturday&rsquo;s league derby trip to Atletico Madrid rapidly approaching.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nTWO OUT OF FOUR TO ACCOMPANY BENZEMA\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nOne player surely set to start is Karim Benzema, who has produced some of the best football of his career over the last month. The French forward has always been a silky-smooth contributor to build-up play, but now he is also adding end product by scoring six goals in his last four games.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nThe bigger question for Solari, however, is who will accompany Benzema on the flanks, with four players &ndash; Marco Asensio, Gareth Bale, Vinicius Junior and Lucas Vazquez &ndash; all available to fill just two places.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nBale has just returned from injury and delivered a disappointing performance in Sunday night&rsquo;s victory over Alaves, being replaced by Asensio &ndash; also coming back after injury &ndash; after an hour. But the only way for Bale to regain rhythm and match fitness is by playing, and Solari therefore could well decide this is the ideal stage for the Welshman to follow the path towards full sharpness.\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, teen sensation Vinicius is hoping to continue his meteoric rise by playing in El Clasico for the very first time, giving him a first real opportunity to shine on a truly global stage. However, he has played a lot of football in recent weeks, starting the last nine games in a row, so this could also be the opportunity for Solari to rest the youngster &ndash; and keep him as a surprise package to spring upon Barca in the second leg or league clash in a few weeks&rsquo; time\r\n\r\n\\r\\n\r\n', 3, 17, 'True', '2019-02-06', '2019-03-31', './images/newsCms/Data/BeFunky-collage-5.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/388090_resized257915.jpg', 0, 'True'),
(512, 'تعرف على قرارات إجتماع “أزمة المؤجلات” في الدوري المصري', '    ', '<p>أعلن أحمد مجاهد عضو مجلس الإدارة والمتحدث الرسمي باسم اتحاد كرة القدم، قرارات ونتائج اجتماع مجلس الجبلاية مع مسئولي أندية الدوري المصري لمناقشة أزمة المباريات المؤجلة. \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n و قال أحمد مجاهد في المؤتمر الصحفي عقب الاجتماع&nbsp; أن مجلس الجبلاية كلف عامر حسين رئيس لجنة المسابقات بدراسة موقف الجدول لجميع الاندية، وعرضه خلال ايام على مجلس الادارة قبل اتخاذ الموقف النهائي. \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n وتابع مجاهد أن اجتماع الجمعية العمومية للجبلاية 23 فبراير سيتم خلاله مناقشة جدول الدوري الممتاز المصري وتقديم المقترحات لانقاذه مؤكدا أن الاجتماع لم يتم خلاله مناقشة تعديل مباراة واحدة بل تم مناقشة تعديل مباريات جميع الأندية. \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n و عن تطبيق الفار قال مجاهد أن هاني أبوريدة رئيس مجلس الادارة و أحمد شوبير نائب الرئيس وعصام عبدالفتاح رئيس لجنة الحكام &nbsp;تناقشوا بشأن امكانية تطبيق الفار في مباريات الدوري المصري إلا أن إمكانيات الملاعب تحول دون تطبيق الخاصية و سيكون هناك محاولات لتطبيقه في كأس أمم أفريقيا 2019. \\\\r\\\\n</p>\\r\\n', 3, 15, 'True', '2019-02-06', '2019-04-29', './images/newsCms/Data/1489342158853239000.jpg', './images/newsCms/Data/thumb/624723_resized478275.jpg', 3, 'True'),
