(9, '2018-07-29', '2018-08-29', ' That\'s just a brief image of what every second of ELFIT', 'Events', 'ELFIT Reebok, an international fitness competition that grew in it&rsquo;s own unique way, launched in Egypt back in February 2013. Just Imagine Hounds of people gathered together, chanting, cheering, all encouraging athletes that are on that battlefield watching them while their pushing through pain, going beyond their limits, giving it their all. That&rsquo;s just a brief image of what ELFIT is like. ELFIT 2017 Finals will be held in Egypt, Giza at Palm Hills Club, from the 12th to the 14th of October 2017. It is created and managed by In The Zone Sports, a leading sports&rsquo; events &amp; management company based in Egypt&nbsp;\nReturning for its 5th season ELFIT promises to raise the bar even higher than last year, bringing you a BIGGER BETTER &amp; HOTTER event. This year the competition will be even tougher with a lot of surprises &amp; higher prizes. The final event total prizes will be more than 25,000 USD in cash. The competition is open to all nationalities; However, all athletes must hold a valid passport or a local Egyptian ID', './images/news_images/image004.png', './images/news_images/thumb/819824_resized406682.jpg', '2018-08-26 10:08:26', '2018-11-27 16:11:56', 1000000, '0', 0, 0),
(10, '2018-07-29', '2018-08-29', 'Cycling ', 'Events', 'Route\nThe 1st stage of the 2018 Tour de France starts on &Icirc;le de Noirmoutier, a small island off the Atlantic coast of France.\nStage 2 runs from Mouilleron-Saint-Germain to La Roche-sur-Yon on gently rolling roads.\nThe 3rd stage is a team trial of 35 kilometres featuring a few short climbs with gradients of approximately 5%.\nThe 4th stage sets off in coastal town La Baule to finish a false flat arrival in Sarzeau.\nStage 5 travels on a hilly route to a trying last kilometre in Quimper\nStage 6&nbsp;takes in a double ascent of the M&ucirc;r-de-Bretagne in&nbsp;\nStage 7 and stage 8 &ndash; both likely candidates for a bunch sprint &ndash; the Tour de France leaves Brittany behind to head for the highlight of the first week of action: cobbles.', './images/news_images/99d4a9fb-e502-46f4-9ca6-3e9a45d37b07.jpg', './images/news_images/thumb/422548_resized565099.jpg', '2018-08-26 10:08:26', '2018-11-27 16:11:56', 1000000, '0', 0, 0),
